|publisher=. Journal of Comparative Fascist Studies|date=2013}}</ref><br />[[Ultranationalism]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.globalproject.info/it/in_movimento/reggio-emilia-contro-ogni-nazionalismo-per-uneuropa-di-diritti-e-dignita/15574|title=Reggio Emilia - Contro ogni nazionalismo, per un'Europa di diritti e dignit\u00e0|website=Global Project}}</ref><br />[[Hard Euroscepticism]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.casapounditalia.org/2014/03/intervista-simone-di-stefano-sullunione.html|title=Intervista a Simone Di Stefano sull'Unione Europea}}</ref><br />[[Souverainism]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.genova24.it/2017/09/estrema-destra-parlano-militanti-della-superba-neofascisti-termine-riduttivo-sovranisti-guardiamo-al-futuro-185878/|title=Estrema destra, parlano i militanti della Superba: \"Neofascisti? Termine riduttivo, siamo sovranisti e guardiamo al futuro\"|author=Katia Bonchi|newspaper=Genova24|date=14 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dagospia.com/rubrica-3/politica/fascisteria-de-rsquo-noantri-ldquo-casa-pound-rdquo-ldquo-forza-149924.htm|title=I movimenti di Ultradestra provano a rifarsi il look come \"sovranisti\" (E qualcuno li vota...)|author=Antonio Rapisarda|website=Dagospia|date=14 June 2017}}</ref><br />[[Opposition to immigration|Anti-immigration]]{{cn|date=August 2019}}<br />[[Anti-capitalism]]<ref>{{Cite book|language=French|author1=Jean-Yves Camus|author2=Nicolas Lebourg|title=Les Droites extr\u00eames en Europe|location=|date=5 November 2015|pages=|isbn=9782021176520|url=https://books.google.com/?id=JgTICgAAQBAJ&pg=PT115&dq=casapound+anticapitaliste#v=onepage&q=anticapitaliste&f=false}}</ref>}}\n| position        = [[Far-right politics|Far-right]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-italy-farright/italys-far-right-makes-inroads-locally-as-nation-frets-about-fascism-idUKKBN1DK1WQ|title=Italy's far-right makes inroads locally as nation frets about fascism|first=Isla|last=Binnie|accessdate=20 September 2018|newspaper=Reuters|date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/english/news/general_news/2018/03/01/far-right-casapound-activist-attacked-3_3bb77bd8-725c-49cd-a331-0cc0b450966a.html|title=Far-right CasaPound activist 'attacked' (3) - English|date=1 March 2018|accessdate=20 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lagazzettadelmezzogiorno.it/news/english/987626/++-far-right-casapound-activist-attacked-in-livorno-++.html|title=++ Far-right CasaPound activist 'attacked in Livorno' ++|accessdate=20 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/news/world/929048/italy-news-italian-election-bomb-casapound-trento|title=Anti-fascists BOMB far-right party headquarters as tensions rise after Italy election|first=Joey|last=Millar|date=8 March 2018|accessdate=20 September 2018}}</ref>\n| european = \n| international   =\n| colours          = {{Color box|{{CasaPound/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} [[Black]] {{Color box|#DC150F|border=darkgray}} [[Red]]\n| seats1_title    = [[Italian Chamber of Deputies|Chamber of Deputies]]\n| seats1          = {{Composition bar|0|630|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n| seats2_title    = [[Italian Senate|Senate]]\n| seats2          = {{Composition bar|0|315|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n| seats3_title    = [[European Parliament]]\n| seats3          = {{Composition bar|0|73|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n| flag            = [[File:Flag CasaPound.png|180px]]\n| website         = {{URL|casapounditalia.org}}\n| country         = Italy\n}}\n\n'''CasaPound Italy''' ({{lang-it|CasaPound Italia}}, CPI; \"House of [[Ezra Pound]]\") is an [[Politics of Italy|Italian]] [[Neo-fascism|neo-fascist]] movement and formerly a [[List of political parties in Italy|political party]] born as a network of [[far-right social centres]] arising from the occupation of a state-owned building by [[squatting|squatters]] in the neighbourhood of [[Esquilino]] in [[Rome]] on 26 December 2003.\n\nSubsequently, the phenomenon spread with other instances of squatting, demonstrations and various initiatives, becoming a [[political movement]].\n\nAs such, in June 2008, CasaPound therefore constituted an \"association of social promotion\", and assumed its current name '''CasaPound Italy \u2013 CPI'''; the party's symbol is the \"Arrowed Turtle\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.casapounditalia.org/p/il-simbolo.html?m=1|title=Il Simbolo|website=www.casapounditalia.org|accessdate=20 September 2018}}</ref> On 26 June 2019, CasaPound's leader Gianluca Iannone announced CasaPound existence as a political party was finished, going back to its original status of social movement. <ref>https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/06/27/news/casapound_torna_movimento_iannone-229739363/</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[image:CasaPound.JPG|thumb|left|CasaPound building in Rome]]\nThe first illegal occupation made using the name CasaPound was on 26 December 2003 in Rome, by a group of young people referring to the ONC/OSA area (acronym for \"Non-Compliant Occupations and Occupations with a Housing Purpose\"), and coming from previous experience of CasaMontag (named after [[Guy Montag]]) at the gates of Rome. The building, a former government building in via Napoleone III, later became the national headquarters of the movement and the association.  In 2010, 23 families and a total of 82 people lived in CasaPound.<ref>{{in lang|it}} Mario Bernardi Guardi, [http://www.iltempo.it/2010/10/22/1211007-mario_bernardi_guardi.shtml?refresh_ce \"Sono fascisti i ragazzi di Casa Pound e del Blocco Studentesco? \u00c8 da qualche anno che politici, giornalisti, sociologi si pongono la domanda ed \u00e8 da qualche anno che non riescono a dare e a darsi una risposta convincente,\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120804135310/http://www.iltempo.it/2010/10/22/1211007-mario_bernardi_guardi.shtml?refresh_ce# |date=4 August 2012 }} Il Tempo (22/10/2010). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref>\n\nPreviously, CasaPound was associated with [[Tricolour Flame]] until 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.casapounditalia.org/p/la-storia.html|title=CasaPound Italia - La storia|language=it|access-date=2017-11-12}}</ref> but now has its own movement, CasaPound Italy, extending all over Italy with many social centres. While CPI does not recognize the classic definitions of right and left,<ref>{{in lang|it}} [http://www.ideodromocasapound.org/?p=674 \"Manifesto dell\u2019Estremocentroalto\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130531102414/http://www.ideodromocasapound.org/?p=674# |date=31 May 2013 }} (18 October 2011). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref> it is commonly placed in the category of the political groups and movements of the Italian [[Radical right (Europe)|radical right]]. Casapound is generally self-defined by its followers as [[Third Position]], however.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/basta-destra-e-sinistra-meglio-etica-epica-ed-estetica.html|title=&quot;Basta con destra e sinistra Meglio etica, epica ed estetica&quot;|work=ilGiornale.it|access-date=2018-03-03|language=it}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011 it was estimated that CasaPound Italy had 5,000 members, while in 2017 they reached 6,000.<ref name=\"Kington-guardian-06-11-2011\">Tom Kington, [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/nov/06/italy-fascists-true-mussolini-ideology \"Italy's fascists stay true to Mussolini's ideology],\"[[The Guardian]] (6 November 2011). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref>\n\nOn 13 November 2017, Simone Di Stefano was elected secretary and nominal prime ministerial candidate for the [[2018 Italian general election|2018 general election]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.casapounditalia.org/2017/11/elezioni-di-stefano-diventa-il.html|title=Elezioni: Di Stefano diventa il segretario di CasaPound e lancia il programma per le politiche|website=www.casapounditalia.org|accessdate=20 September 2018}}</ref> although the party subsequently formally stated that it hoped [[Lega Nord|Northern League]] leader [[Matteo Salvini]] became Prime Minister.<ref>{{cite news|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|title=Fascists throw support behind hard-Right party in Silvio Berlusconi's alliance ahead of Italian election|date=26 February 2018|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/02/26/fascists-throw-support-behind-hard-right-party-silvio-berlusconis/}}</ref>\n\nIn order to participate in the [[2019 European Parliament election in Italy]], an electoral joint list was formed by CasaPound together with [[United Right (Italy)|United Right]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.affaritaliani.it/politica/elezioni-europee-2019-casapound-in-lizza-con-le-destre-unite-598085.html|title=Elezioni Europee 2019: CasaPound in lizza con Destre Unite|website=Affaritaliani.it}}</ref> CasaPound leader [[Simone Di Stefano]] topped the coalition's list however the coalition was unable to win any seats in the [[European Parliament]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rerumromanarum.com/2019/04/casapound-italia-destre-unite-i.html|title=CasaPound Italia - Destre Unite - I candidati - Speciale Europee 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Ideology ==\nOne feature of this movement, according to sociologist Emanuele Toscano, is to present a different interpretation of [[fascism]] aimed at overcoming the dichotomy of right-left.<ref>Emanuele Toscano & Daniele Di Nunzio [http://isa2010.aimit.se/146470/Paper \"Can We Still Speak about Extreme Right Movements? Casapound in Italy between Community and Subjectivation Drives,\"] XVII World Congress of Sociology (14 July 2010). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref> The political position of CasaPound is based on the fascist [[Third Position]], defined as \"extreme-upper-centre\" by the movement itself.<ref>{{cite news|URL=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/basta-destra-e-sinistra-meglio-etica-epica-ed-estetica.html|title=\"Basta con destra e sinistra Meglio etica, epica ed estetica\"|newspaper=[[il Giornale]]|date=10 April 2009}}</ref>\n\nThe name, inspired by the poet [[Ezra Pound]], refers to his ''[[The Cantos|Cantos]]'' against usury, criticisms of the economic positions of both [[capitalism]] and [[Marxism]], and his membership of the [[Italian Social Republic]]. It also gives particular attention to the [[Congress of Verona (1943)|Manifesto of Verona]], the [[Labour Charter of 1927]] and social legislation of fascism.<ref>{{cite news|URL=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2017/06/21/saluti-romani-e-un-tocco-di-glamour-ecco-la-casapound10.html|title=Saluti romani e un tocco di glamour ecco la nuova strategia di CasaPound|author=Paolo Berizzi|newspaper=[[la Repubblica]]|date=21 June 2017}}</ref> There has been collaboration with the [[identitarian movement]] which propagates a [[White people|white]], [[Christianity|Christian]] Europe.<ref>Eleonora Vio, [http://www.dagospia.com/rubrica-3/politica/arrivano-nazi-pop-austria-movimento-ultradestra-identitare-129453.htm  \"Arrivano i Nazi-Pop\"], dagospia.com, 26 Jul 2016.</ref> The movement also claim the legacy of far-left figures, like [[Che Guevara]]<ref>{{cite news|URL=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2017/10/17/casapound-e-la-volta-di-porro-scontro-su-che-guevara-per-voi-e-un-modello-ma-a-me-ha-rotto-le-palle-tutta-linfanzia/3918323/|title=Casapound, \u00e8 la volta di Porro. Scontro su Che Guevara: \"Per voi \u00e8 un modello, ma a me ha rotto le palle per tutta l\u2019infanzia\"|author=Angela Gennaro|publisher=[[il Fatto Quotidiano]]|date=17 October 2017}}</ref> and [[Hugo Ch\u00e1vez]].<ref>{{cite news|URL=http://www.blitzquotidiano.it/foto-notizie/patria-socialismo-muerte-casa-pound-ricorda-chavez-striscioni-50-citta-1499402/|title=\"Patria, socialismo o muerte\". Casa Pound ricorda Chavez: striscioni in 50 citt\u00e0|publisher=Blitz|date=11 March 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn social and domestic issues, CasaPound has a strong [[Opposition to immigration|anti-immigration]] rhetoric,<ref>{{cite news|URL=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/nov/06/italy-fascists-true-mussolini-ideology|title=Italy's fascists stay true to Mussolini's ideology|author=Tom Kington|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=6 November 2011}}</ref> but lack of homogeneity on other themes. In January 2016, many members of the movement participated in the ''Family Day'', supporting the [[traditional family]] idea.<ref>{{cite news|URL=http://www.ilprimatonazionale.it/cronaca/di-stefano-casapound-sara-al-family-day-la-bandiera-arcobaleno-si-sconfigge-col-tricolore-38759/|title=Di Stefano: \"CasaPound sar\u00e0 al Family Day, la bandiera arcobaleno si sconfigge col tricolore\"|newspaper=Primato Nazionale|date=26 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|URL=http://www.corriere.it/politica/16_gennaio_27/al-family-day-anche-casa-pound-organizzatori-non-li-vogliamo-76493046-c464-11e5-8e0c-7baf441d5d56.shtml|title=Al Family day anche Casa Pound. Gli organizzatori: non li vogliamo|author=Alessandro Trocino|newspaper=[[Corriere della Sera]]|date=26 January 2016}}</ref> In 2017, the establishment of CasaPound expressed support to the [[same-sex marriage]], [[Advance healthcare directive|advance directive]] and improvement of the [[welfare state]].<ref>{{cite news|URL=http://espresso.repubblica.it/palazzo/2012/02/08/news/roma-casapound-spiazza-tutti-1.40175|title=Roma, Casapound spiazza tutti|author=Alessandro Capriccioli|magazine=[[l'Espresso]]|date=8 February 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.affaritaliani.it/politica/casa-pound-sondaggi-elezioni-ostia-m5s-parlamento-fascismo-matrimoni-gay-506547.html?refresh_ce|title=M5s gi\u00e0 vecchio: CasaPound \u00e8 la novit\u00e0 che aspira a entrare in Parlamento|author=Marco Zonetti|website=Affari Italiani.it|date=26 October 2017}}</ref> The party supports [[abortion]] rights.<ref>{{cite news|URL=https://jacobitemag.com/2018/02/01/a-field-guide-to-the-italian-new-right/|title=A Field Guide to the Italian New Right|newspaper=Jacobite}}</ref> Some activists of the movement expressed [[antisemitic]] and [[xenophobic]] rhetoric online,<ref>{{cite book|url=http://cadmus.eui.eu/bitstream/handle/1814/26448/477a_Populism_Italy_web.pdf|title=Populism in Europe: CasaPound|author1=Jamie Bartlett|author2=Jonathan Birdwell|author3=Caterina Froio|publisher=[[Demos (UK think tank)|Demos]]|date=2012}}</ref> but CasaPound refuses both and expels members who support these ideas.<ref>{{cite news|URL=http://www.fascinazione.info/2013/01/casapound-mette-alla-porta-i-militanti.html|title=CasaPound mette alla porta i militanti che non rifiutano antisemitismo e razzismo|newspaper=FascinAzione|date=24 January 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn foreign policy, CasaPound is critical of the [[European Union]], instead supporting a communitarian-nationalist Europe.<ref>{{cite news|URL=http://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/politica/11710331/Casapound--l-intervista-a-Gianluca.html|title=Casapound, l'intervista a Gianluca Iannone: \"Il nostro nemico comune \u00e8 questa Unione Europea\"|newspaper=[[Libero (newspaper)|Libero]]|date=21 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=iX6KAVV4MFEC&pg=PA13&lpg=PA13&dq=casapound+europeismo#v=onepage&q=casapound%20europeismo&f=false|title=Dentro e fuori CasaPound: capire il fascismo del terzo millennio|author1=Daniele Di Nunzio|author2=Emanuele Toscano|publisher=Armando Editore|date=2011|isbn=9788860819260}}</ref> The Movement was originally both [[anti-American]]<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=HpUXx1lNSAgC&pg=PT33&lpg=PT33&dq=casapound+antiamericani#v=onepage&q=casapound%20antiamericani&f=false|title=L'orda nera|author1=Antonella Grippo|author2=Giovanni Fasanella|publisher=Bur|date=2009|isbn=9788858650455}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|URL=https://www.questotrentino.it/articolo/12209/una_nuova_destra_giovane_e_confusa.htm|title=Una nuova destra, giovane e confusa|author1=Luca Facchini|author2=Alberto Gianera|newspaper=QuestoTrentino|date=2 July 2011}}</ref> and [[anti-Zionist]],<ref>{{cite news|URL=http://www.iltempo.it/politica/2014/01/29/gallery/saremo-pure-antisionisti-ma-non-spediamo-teste-di-maiale-925009/|title=\"Saremo pure antisionisti ma non spediamo teste di maiale\"|newspaper=[[Il Tempo]]|date=29 January 2014}}</ref> and started a cooperation with the Lebanese [[Anti-imperialism|anti-imperialist]], [[Anti-Zionism|anti-Zionist]] [[Hezbollah]] organization in 2015.<ref>{{cite news|URL=http://roma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2015/09/20/news/roma_convegno_mediterraneo_solidale_iniziativa_fascio-islamica-123310960/|title=Roma, la strana coppia Hezbollah-Casapound insieme al convegno|author=Corrado Zunino|newspaper=[[la Repubblica]]|date=20 September 2015}}</ref> However, Di Stefano later said, \"we do not have problems with Israel\".<ref>{{cite book|title=The Identitarians|first= Jos\u00e9|last=Pedro Z\u00faquete|year=2018|quote=\"We are not racists, we are not anti-Semitic, we do not have problems with Israel,\" said Simone Di Stefano, CasaPound's vice president, when its then-political ally Matteo Salvini was denied entry into Israel on the purported basis of his CasaPound connection.}}</ref> In 2018, Di Stefano defended Israeli Prime Minister [[Benjamin Netanyahu]]'s policies regarding repatriation of illegal immigrants to Africa as \"undoubtedly excellent\", and criticised humanitarian organisations and the [[United Nations]] for intervening to prevent them.<ref>{{cite news|work=Lo Speciale|title=Israele-migranti, per Di Stefano (CasaPound): \"E\u2019 colpa delle Ong\"|date=3 April 2018|url=https://www.lospecialegiornale.it/2018/04/03/migranti-israele-casapound/}}</ref> Di Stefano has expressed support for U.S. President [[Donald Trump]], but requested that he close U.S. military bases in Italy.<ref>{{cite news|work=[[Libero (newspaper)|Libero]]|title=CasaPound, l'orgoglio di Di Stefano: \"Siamo fascisti, ammiro Putin\"|date=16 November 2017|url=https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/politica/13280561/casapound-simone-di-stefano-siamo-fascisti-stimiamo-putin-trump-razzismo-immigrazione-euro-.html}}</ref>\n\n==Activities==\n[[File:Manifestazione Napoli 2011.jpg|thumb|250px|CasaPound rally in [[Naples]].]]\nThe social centre has its own musical band, [[Zetazeroalfa]], an association of [[civil protection]] and promotes sports ([[hiking]], [[parachuting]], [[Underwater diving|diving]] and other disciplines), union activities, and recreational activities, including a theater company, web radio, web television and a monthly magazine.\n\nCasaPound has promoted initiatives outside the Italian territory through its non-profit organization Solidarit\u00e9 Identit\u00e9s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.solidarite-identites.org/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=18 January 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130204005140/http://www.solidarite-identites.org/ |archive-date=4 February 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The activities of the movement have been the subject of attention by some foreign media.<ref name=\"Giulia-Basile-3sat\">{{in lang|de}} Giulia Basile, [http://www.3sat.de/page/?source=/kulturzeit/themen/152484/index.html \"Mussolinis Enkel. \"Casa Pounds\" rechte Jugendzentren in Italien,\"] 3sat.de (07.03.2011). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref><ref name=\"rt-italian-far-right\">[http://rt.com/news/italy-crisis-right/ \"Italian far right get boost amidst country's economic troubles,\"] RT (7 March 2011). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svoboda.org/a/2311033.html|title=\u041c\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043e\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438 \u0432\u043c\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0411\u0435\u0440\u043b\u0443\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043d\u0438?|website=\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e \u0421\u0432\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0434\u0430}}</ref>\n\nFrom the period of activity of the first social centre then were organized and cultural meetings with several guests, including writer [[Nicolai Lilin]],<ref>{{in lang|it}} Spadaccino Maria Rosaria, [http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2009/settembre/10/Nicolai_Lilin_Andare_CasaPound_dovere_co_9_090910075.shtml \"Nicolai Lilin: \u00abAndare a CasaPound \u00e8 un dovere\u00bb,\"] Corriere della Sera (10 September 2009). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref> the [[LGBT]] deputy [[Paola Concia]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altroquotidiano.it/?p=13651|title=++ Carabinieri e Gdf a Roma negli uffici della Consip ++ \u2013 L'altroquotidiano.it|website=www.altroquotidiano.it}}</ref> an ex-[[Red Brigades]] [[Valerio Morucci]],<ref>{{in lang|it}} [http://www.unita.it/italia/morucci-a-casapound-folla-lo-applaude-nemici-ma-senza-discriminazione-1.26961 \"Morucci a Casapound: folla lo applaude, nemici ma senza discriminazione,\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121116104813/http://www.unita.it/italia/morucci-a-casapound-folla-lo-applaude-nemici-ma-senza-discriminazione-1.26961# |date=16 November 2012 }} L'Unita (6 February 2009). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref> and the [[Chinese people|Chinese]] community.<ref>{{in lang|it}} Ilaria Misantoni, [http://www.teverenotizie.it/conferenza-tra-casapound-e-comunita-cinese-di-roma-del-19-dicembre-2011,A1,2619.html \"CasaPound incontra la comunit\u00e0 cinese,\"] (20 December 2011). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref>\n\nThe main CasaPound political proposal is the so-called ''Mutuo Sociale'' (''Social Mortgage''),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mutuosociale.org/|title=Mutuo Sociale|website=www.mutuosociale.org}}</ref> as a response to the problem of housing which, according to official data, involving approximately 23,000 households throughout Italy. In October 2011, the Lazio Region officially approved it within its \"House Plan\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.regione.lazio.it/rl_main/|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120911134837/http://www.regione.lazio.it/consiglioweb/dettaglio_comunicati.php?vms=172&vmf=&id=2165|url-status=dead|title=Sito ufficiale della Regione Lazio - Home Page|website=www.regione.lazio.it|access-date=13 March 2019|archive-date=11 September 2012}}</ref>\n\nStarting with the 2011 elections CasaPound presented their candidates in local elections in civic lists or centre-right and succeeded in electing its representatives.<ref>{{in lang|it}} [http://www.agenparl.it/articoli/news/politica/20110519-amministrative-casapound-cinque-consiglieri-eletti \" Amministrative: CasaPound, Cinque Consiglieri Eletti,\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121116190122/http://www.agenparl.it/articoli/news/politica/20110519-amministrative-casapound-cinque-consiglieri-eletti# |date=16 November 2012 }} agenparl.it (19 May 2011). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref> At regional and national elections of 2013 CasaPound Italy announced that it will present its civic lists throughout Italy.\n\n==Youth wing==\n[[File:Blocco Studentesco.png|thumb|right|150px|Logo of ''Blocco Studentesco'', the youth wing of CasaPound.]]\nIn 2006, the movement that arose around the first community centre was endowed with its student organization, under the name Students' Block ({{lang-it|Blocco Studentesco}}).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://libcom.org/library/casa-pound-new-radical-right-italy|title=Casa Pound and the new radical right in Italy|website=libcom.org}}</ref> Francesco Polacchi is the General Secretary of Students' Block.\n\nTheir logo resembles [[Flash and Circle|that]] of the [[British Union of Fascists]].\n\nQuestions have been submitted by parliamentarians of the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] about fascist propaganda and the violence of the student movement.<ref>{{in lang|it}} Giuseppe Berretta, [http://www.giuseppeberretta.it/documenti/interr_univ_casapound.doc \"Interrogazione Parlamentare PD contro il Blocco Studentesco\"] (21 April 2010).</ref>\n\n==International meetings==\nOver the years the leaders of CasaPound Italy have been invited to explain its \u201cpolitical model\u201d in many of the major European capitals ([[Paris]], [[Madrid]], [[London]], [[Lisbon]], [[Brussels]], [[Warsaw]])<ref>{{in lang|it}} [http://www.agenziastampaitalia.it/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4975:casapound-italia-in-1500-alla-festa-nazionale&catid=4:politica-nazionale&Itemid=34 \"CasaPound Italia: in 1.500 alla festa nazionale\"] (21 September 2011). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref> and the organization has been the subject of some reports by foreign media.<ref name=\"Giulia-Basile-3sat\"/><ref name=\"rt-italian-far-right\"/>\n\nIn 2011 the [[Finnish Resistance Movement]] also invited members of CasaPound to a seminar in [[Helsinki]].<ref>[http://yle.fi/uutiset/city_of_helsinki_rented_space_to_neo-nazi_group/5445909 \"City of Helsinki rented space to neo-Nazi group,\"] YLE News (31.10.2011). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref> This shows an ability of the European nationalists to organize beyond ideological differences. The Finnish Resistance Movement represents [[national socialism]].<ref>{{in lang|fi}} Mikael Brunila, [http://suomenkuvalehti.fi/jutut/kotimaa/ei-ole-yhta-aarioikeistoa-keita-suomen-vastarintaliike-kutsui-helsinkiin \"Ei ole yht\u00e4 \u00e4\u00e4rioikeistoa - keit\u00e4 Suomen vastarintaliike kutsui Helsinkiin?,\"] Suomen Kuvalehti (21.10.2011; uptaded: 29 November 2013). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref> The [[Finnish Security Intelligence Service]] researched the connections of the Finnish Resistance Movement to CasaPound after the [[2011 Florence shootings]].<ref>[http://yle.fi/uutiset/supo_looks_into_possible_finnish_connection_to_florence_shooter/5468477 \"Supo looks into possible Finnish connection to Florence shooter,\"] YLE (15.12.2011). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref>\n\n==Symbolic figures==\n\nThe party's choice of American poet [[Ezra Pound]] as a symbol of the movement has caused controversy with his daughter, [[Mary de Rachewiltz]], who claimed it distorts the meaning of Pound's work and represents a \"misappropriation\" of his image,<ref>Tom Kingtom, [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2012/jan/14/ezra-pound-daughter-fascism \"Ezra Pound's daughter fights to wrest the renegade poet's legacy from fascists,\"] The Observer (14 January 2012). Retrieved 14 December 2013.</ref> despite Pound's stated support for fascism.\n\n==Electoral results==\n===Italian Parliament===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"width:50%; border:1px #AAAAFF solid\"\n|-\n| colspan=7|[[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n|-\n! width=13%|Election year\n! width=16%|Votes\n! width=6%|% \n! width=1%|Seats\n! width=8%|+/\u2013\n! width=18%|Leader\n|-\n! [[2013 Italian general election|2013]]\n| 47,691 (20th)\n| 0.14\n| {{Composition bar|0|630|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n| <center>\u2013</center>\n| <center>Gianluca Iannone</center>\n|-\n! [[2018 Italian general election|2018]]\n| 312,432 (10th)\n| 0.95\n| {{Composition bar|0|630|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n| <center>\u2013</center>\n| <center>Simone Di Stefano</center>\n|}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"width:50%; border:1px #AAAAFF solid\"\n|-\n| colspan=7|[[Senate of the Republic (Italy)|Senate of the Republic]]\n|-\n! width=13%|Election year\n! width=16%|Votes\n! width=6%|% \n! width=1%|Seats\n! width=8%|+/\u2013\n! width=18%|Leader\n|-\n! [[2013 Italian general election|2013]]\n| 40,540 (20th)\n| 0.13\n| {{Composition bar|0|315|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n| <center>\u2013</center>\n| <center>Gianluca Iannone</center>\n|-\n! [[2018 Italian general election|2018]]\n| 259,718 (10th)\n| 0.86\n| {{Composition bar|0|315|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n| <center>\u2013</center>\n| <center>Simone Di Stefano</center>\n|}\n\n=== European Parliament ===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"width:50%; border:1px #AAAAFF solid\"\n|-\n| colspan=7|[[European Parliament]]\n|-\n! width=13%|Election year\n! width=16%|Votes\n! width=6%|% \n! width=1%|Seats\n! width=8%|+/\u2013\n! width=18%|Leader\n|-\n![[2019 European Parliament election in Italy|2019]]\n| 89,142\t\n|0.33\n|{{Composition bar|0|72|hex=darkblue}}\n|<center>''new''</center>\n|Simone Di Stefano<br>Massimiliano Panero\n|}\n\n===Regional Councils===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"width:50%; border:1px #AAAAFF solid\"\n|-\n! width=19%|Region\n! width=13%|Election year\n! width=16%|Votes\n! width=7%|% \n! width=1%|Seats\n! width=6%|+/\u2013\n|-\n![[Lombardy]]\n![[2018 Lombard regional election|2018]]\n|45,416\n|0.86\n|{{Composition bar|0|80|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n|<center>\u2013</center>\n|-\n! [[Umbria]]\n! [[2015 Umbrian regional election|2015]]\n| 2,343\n| 0.66\n| {{Composition bar|0|20|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n| <center>\u2013</center>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" |[[Lazio]]\n![[2013 Lazio regional election|2013]]\n|18,491\n|0.66\n|{{Composition bar|0|50|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n|<center>\u2013</center>\n|-\n![[2018 Lazio regional election|2018]]\n| 42,609\n| 1.68\n|{{Composition bar|0|50|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n|<center>\u2013</center>\n|-\n![[Abruzzo]]\n![[2019 Abruzzo regional election|2019]]\n|2,974\n|0.47\n|{{Composition bar|0|31|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n|<center>\u2013</center>\n|-\n! [[Molise]]\n! [[2018 Molise regional election|2018]]\n| 477\n| 0.33\n| {{Composition bar|0|21|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n| <center>\u2013</center>\n|-\n! [[South Tyrol]]\n! [[2018 Trentino-Alto Adige/S\u00fcdtirol provincial elections|2018]]\n| 2,451\n| 0.86\n| {{Composition bar|0|35|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n| <center>\u2013</center>\n|-\n! [[Trentino]]\n! [[2018 Trentino-Alto Adige/S\u00fcdtirol provincial elections|2018]]\n| 1,215\n| 0.48\n| {{Composition bar|0|35|hex={{CasaPound/meta/color}}}}\n| <center>\u2013</center>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Far-right social centres]]\n* [[Social Bastion]]\n* [[New Force (Italy)|New Force]]\n* [[Neo-fascism]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* [http://www.casapounditalia.org/ CasaPound website]\n* [http://www.bloccostudentesco.org/ Blocco Studentesco - official website]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lvZtoVIECuo CasaPound Nationalist Squat in Rome] on YouTube\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I3x-ge4w46E The hipster fascists trying to bring Mussolini back into the mainstream] on YouTube\n* [http://www.radixjournal.com/altright-archive/altright-archive/main/the-magazine/in-the-house-of-pound/ English interview with the leader of Casa Pound]\n\n{{Italian political parties}}\n{{White nationalism}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Political movements in Italy]]\n[[Category:Social centres]]\n[[Category:Squats in Italy]]\n[[Category:Far-right politics in Italy]]\n[[Category:Third Position]]\n[[Category:Opposition to Islam in Italy]]\n[[Category:Nationalist parties in Italy]]\n[[Category:Eurosceptic parties in Italy]]\n[[Category:Organizations that oppose same-sex marriage]]\n[[Category:Neo-fascist organisations in Italy]]\n[[Category:Far-right parties in Europe]]\n[[Category:Far-right movements in Europe]]\n[[Category:Right-wing anti-capitalism]]\n[[Category:2003 establishments in Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox Political Party\n| name            = CasaPound Italy\n| native_name     = CasaPound Italia\n| colorcode       = {{CasaPound/meta/color}}\n| logo            = [[File:CasaPound Italia.png|170px]]\n| leader1_title   = President\n| leader1_name    = Gianluca Iannone\n| leader2_title   = Secretary\n| leader2_name    = Simone Di Stefano\n| foundation      = {{start date|df=y|2003|12|26}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fascinazione.info/2016/12/26-dicembre-2003-nel-cuore-di-roma.html|title=26 Dicembre 2003: Nel Cuore Di Roma Nasce CasaPound|author=Giuseppe Parente|website=FascinAzione|date=26 December 2016}}</ref>\n| headquarters    = Via Napoleone III n. 8, [[Rome]]\n| youth_wing      = [[Students' Block]]\n| membership      = 6,000<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.casapounditalia.org/2017/01/casapound-quasi-seimila-iscritti-in-48.html|title=CasaPound: quasi seimila iscritti in 48 ore, risultato da record per la festa del tesseramento|publisher=CasaPound Italia|date=16 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web  |url=http://reconquista-europe.tumblr.com/post/139489377601/interview-with-sebastien-casapound-italia  |pub