{"title_page": "Remember My Name", "text_new": "{{use mdy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Remember My Name\n| image          = Poster of the movie Remember My Name.jpg\n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Alan Rudolph]]\n| producer       = [[Robert Altman]]\n| writer         = Alan Rudolph\n| starring       = [[Geraldine Chaplin]]<br>[[Anthony Perkins]]<br>[[Moses Gunn]]<br>[[Berry Berenson]]<br>[[Jeff Goldblum]]<br>[[Dennis Franz]]\n| music          = [[Alberta Hunter]]\n| cinematography = [[Tak Fujimoto]]\n| editing        = William A. Sawyer<br>Tom Walls\n| distributor    = [[Columbia Pictures]]\n| released       = October 1, 1978\n| runtime        = 94 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| awards         =\n| language       = English\n| budget         =\n| gross          = \n| preceded_by    =\n| followed_by    =\n}}\n\n'''''Remember My Name''''' is a 1978 American [[thriller film]] written and directed by [[Alan Rudolph]] and produced by [[Robert Altman]].  [[Geraldine Chaplin]] stars as a deranged woman, determined to get back her husband, [[Anthony Perkins]].\n\nRudolph explained what he wanted to achieve: \"an update of the classic woman's melodramas of the [[Bette Davis]], [[Barbara Stanwyck]], [[Joan Crawford]] era\".<ref>Rosenbaum, Jonathan. \"Remember My Name\". ''[[Film Quarterly]]''. Vol. 32, no. 3, Spring, 1979</ref> It had a successful run in [[Paris]] before opening in [[New York City]].\n\n==Plot==\nNeil Curry (Perkins) is living a happy life with his second wife Barbara (Berenson) in [[California]] after abandoning his first wife, Emily (Chaplin), in [[New York (state)|New York]]. Their life of domestic bliss is interrupted when Emily comes back from prison, where she served a 12-year sentence for murdering Neil's former lover. She arrives in California to wreak havoc and also to claim back Neil.<ref>{{cite news |last=Flatley |first=Guy |title=At The Movies |page=64 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=December 16, 1977 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1977/12/16/archives/at-the-movies-tony-perkins-goes-from-callow-troubles-to-more-mature.html |accessdate=July 30, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Geraldine Chaplin]] as Emily - Ex-con & Ex-wife\n*[[Anthony Perkins]] as Neil Curry - Husband\n*[[Moses Gunn]] as Pike - Rent Manager\n*[[Berry Berenson]] as Barbara Curry - New wife\n*[[Jeff Goldblum]] as Mr Nudd  - Boss\n*[[Tim Thomerson]] as Jeff - Rita's Boyfriend\n*[[Alfre Woodard]] as Rita - Co-worker\n*[[Marilyn Coleman]] as Teresa\n*[[Jeff Perry (American actor)|Jeff Perry]] as Harry\n*[[Alan Autry]] as Rusty - Teen Co-worker\n*[[Dennis Franz]] as Franks - Waiter\n*[[Jette Seear]] as Saleslady\n\n==Reception==\nThe ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' gave the film 4 out of 5 stars. They praised Perkins and described Chaplin's performance as \"extraordinary\", and that she \"adopts a unique speech pattern as Emily. She says everything as though she's rehearsed it and now is blurting it out in what she hopes will be accepted as a reasonable replica of casual speech. Emily's manner only loses its furtive, dodging quality when she feels in control or when she flies into a rage.\" The review also praises how Rudolph \"embellishes his film with sardonic humour\", and the \"comically macabre touch\" of TV news in the background of disasters such as an earthquake that killed 1 million in [[Budapest]].<ref>LaSalle, Mick. ''Mr. Perkins and the Vicious Stalker''. ''San Francisco Chronicle''. January 13, 1995.</ref>\n\n''[[The Washington Post]]'' described it as a \"neurotic film noir\" that is also a \"gripping tale of sexual frustration\". The reviewer was also impressed with Chaplin's performance; \"Chaplin is spooky, spookier even than Perkins, in this complex performance as a woman who's painfully adjusting to freedom.\"<ref>Kempley, Rita. ''Weekend at the Movies; \"Remember My Name\"''. ''The Washington Post''. September 6, 1985</ref> [[Jack Kroll]] of ''[[Newsweek]]'' praised Rudolph's direction; \"he has a real eye for the visual paradox, the elegant and even beautiful form in which this savagery sometimes works.\" The review praised Perkins as a \"specialist at playing the 'nice guy' whose smile and sweat suggest something not so nice underneath\". Kroll also heaped praise on Chaplin as her performance \"creates something new in the modern pantheon of weirdos. She is chilling in her ability to be both guilty and innocent, victim and predator, catatonic and driven by feelings so deep they draw blood\".<ref>Kroll, Jack. \"Hell Hath No Fury Like A Woman\". ''Newsweek''. April 2, 1978. p. 82B</ref>\n\n===Soundtrack===\n\nThe soundtrack for the film was made up of songs written for the film and original recordings of songs by the singer and composer Alberta Hunter. Alberta Hunter was a veteran of the 1920s \u2013 1930s nightclub scene and Broadway, appearing in the musicals Shuffle Along and Showboat with the London cast.  Hunter, who was 82 at the time, was in the midst of a musical reemergence when the film was released having left show business for twenty years, after the death of her mother, to become a nurse.<ref>The New York Times said this about the recording, \"...produced by John Hammond and featuring sympathetic support by outstanding jazz musicians, can be savored without reference to the film. Indeed, the recording stands autonomously as one of the most relaxed and vibrant blues/jazz sessions released in the past year.\"</ref> [https://www.nytimes.com/1979/06/03/archives/the-robust-artistry-of-alberta-hunter.html The Robust Artistry of Alberta Hunter]\n\nSoundtrack: \n\n1 Workin' Man\n2 You Gotta Reap What You Sow\n3 Love I Have for You\n4 I've Got a Mind to Ramble\n5 Remember My Name\n6 My Castle's Rockin'\n7 Downhearted Blues\n8 Some Sweet Day\n9 Chirpin' the Blues\n10 I Begged and Begged You\n\n===Awards===\n'''[[Miami International Film Festival]]'''\n*1978: \"Best Actress\" \u2013 Geraldine Chaplin\n\n'''[[Festival du Film de Paris|Paris Film Festival]]'''\n*1978: \"Best Actress\" \u2013 Geraldine Chaplin\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|0078150|Remember My Name}}\n*{{rotten-tomatoes|remember_my_name}}\n* {{Amg movie|107572|Remember My Name}}\n*{{tcmdb title|id=3909|title=Remember My Name}}\n\n{{Alan Rudolph}}\n\n[[Category:1978 films]]\n[[Category:1970s thriller films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American thriller films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Alan Rudolph]]\n[[Category:American films about revenge]]\n[[Category:Films about stalking]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n", "text_old": "{{use mdy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Remember My Name\n| image          = Poster of the movie Remember My Name.jpg\n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Alan Rudolph]]\n| producer       = [[Robert Altman]]\n| writer         = Alan Rudolph\n| starring       = [[Geraldine Chaplin]]<br>[[Anthony Perkins]]<br>[[Moses Gunn]]<br>[[Berry Berenson]]<br>[[Jeff Goldblum]]<br>[[Dennis Franz]]\n| music          = [[Alberta Hunter]]\n| cinematography = [[Tak Fujimoto]]\n| editing        = William A. Sawyer<br>Tom Walls\n| distributor    = [[Columbia Pictures]]\n| released       = October 1, 1978 (United States)\n| runtime        = 94 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| awards         =\n| language       = English\n| budget         =\n| gross          = \n| preceded_by    =\n| followed_by    =\n}}\n\n'''''Remember My Name''''' is a 1978 American [[thriller film]] written and directed by [[Alan Rudolph]] and produced by [[Robert Altman]].  [[Geraldine Chaplin]] stars as a deranged woman, determined to get back her husband, [[Anthony Perkins]].\n\nRudolph explained what he wanted to achieve: \"an update of the classic woman's melodramas of the [[Bette Davis]], [[Barbara Stanwyck]], [[Joan Crawford]] era\".<ref>Rosenbaum, Jonathan. \"Remember My Name\". ''[[Film Quarterly]]''. Vol. 32, no. 3, Spring, 1979</ref> It had a successful run in [[Paris]] before opening in [[New York City]].\n\n==Plot==\nNeil Curry (Perkins) is living a happy life with his second wife Barbara (Berenson) in [[California]] after abandoning his first wife, Emily (Chaplin), in [[New York (state)|New York]]. Their life of domestic bliss is interrupted when Emily comes back from prison, where she served a 12-year sentence for murdering Neil's former lover. She arrives in California to wreak havoc and also to claim back Neil.<ref>{{cite news |last=Flatley |first=Guy |title=At The Movies |page=64 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=December 16, 1977 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1977/12/16/archives/at-the-movies-tony-perkins-goes-from-callow-troubles-to-more-mature.html |accessdate=July 30, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Geraldine Chaplin]] as Emily - Ex-con & Ex-wife\n*[[Anthony Perkins]] as Neil Curry - Husband\n*[[Moses Gunn]] as Pike - Rent Manager\n*[[Berry Berenson]] as Barbara Curry - New wife\n*[[Jeff Goldblum]] as Mr Nudd  - Boss\n*[[Tim Thomerson]] as Jeff - Rita's Boyfriend\n*[[Alfre Woodard]] as Rita - Co-worker\n*[[Marilyn Coleman]] as Teresa\n*[[Jeff Perry (American actor)|Jeff Perry]] as Harry\n*[[Alan Autry]] as Rusty - Teen Co-worker\n*[[Dennis Franz]] as Franks - Waiter\n*[[Jette Seear]] as Saleslady\n\n==Reception==\nThe ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' gave the film 4 out of 5 stars. They praised Perkins and described Chaplin's performance as \"extraordinary\", and that she \"adopts a unique speech pattern as Emily. She says everything as though she's rehearsed it and now is blurting it out in what she hopes will be accepted as a reasonable replica of casual speech. Emily's manner only loses its furtive, dodging quality when she feels in control or when she flies into a rage.\" The review also praises how Rudolph \"embellishes his film with sardonic humour\", and the \"comically macabre touch\" of TV news in the background of disasters such as an earthquake that killed 1 million in [[Budapest]].<ref>LaSalle, Mick. ''Mr. Perkins and the Vicious Stalker''. ''San Francisco Chronicle''. January 13, 1995.</ref>\n\n''[[The Washington Post]]'' described it as a \"neurotic film noir\" that is also a \"gripping tale of sexual frustration\". The reviewer was also impressed with Chaplin's performance; \"Chaplin is spooky, spookier even than Perkins, in this complex performance as a woman who's painfully adjusting to freedom.\"<ref>Kempley, Rita. ''Weekend at the Movies; \"Remember My Name\"''. ''The Washington Post''. September 6, 1985</ref> [[Jack Kroll]] of ''[[Newsweek]]'' praised Rudolph's direction; \"he has a real eye for the visual paradox, the elegant and even beautiful form in which this savagery sometimes works.\" The review praised Perkins as a \"specialist at playing the 'nice guy' whose smile and sweat suggest something not so nice underneath\". Kroll also heaped praise on Chaplin as her performance \"creates something new in the modern pantheon of weirdos. She is chilling in her ability to be both guilty and innocent, victim and predator, catatonic and driven by feelings so deep they draw blood\".<ref>Kroll, Jack. \"Hell Hath No Fury Like A Woman\". ''Newsweek''. April 2, 1978. p. 82B</ref>\n\n===Soundtrack===\n\nThe soundtrack for the film was made up of songs written for the film and original recordings of songs by the singer and composer Alberta Hunter. Alberta Hunter was a veteran of the 1920s \u2013 1930s nightclub scene and Broadway, appearing in the musicals Shuffle Along and Showboat with the London cast.  Hunter, who was 82 at the time, was in the midst of a musical reemergence when the film was released having left show business for twenty years, after the death of her mother, to become a nurse.<ref>The New York Times said this about the recording, \"...produced by John Hammond and featuring sympathetic support by outstanding jazz musicians, can be savored without reference to the film. Indeed, the recording stands autonomously as one of the most relaxed and vibrant blues/jazz sessions released in the past year.\"</ref> [https://www.nytimes.com/1979/06/03/archives/the-robust-artistry-of-alberta-hunter.html The Robust Artistry of Alberta Hunter]\n\nSoundtrack: \n\n1 Workin' Man\n2 You Gotta Reap What You Sow\n3 Love I Have for You\n4 I've Got a Mind to Ramble\n5 Remember My Name\n6 My Castle's Rockin'\n7 Downhearted Blues\n8 Some Sweet Day\n9 Chirpin' the Blues\n10 I Begged and Begged You\n\n===Awards===\n'''[[Miami International Film Festival]]'''\n*1978: \"Best Actress\" \u2013 Geraldine Chaplin\n\n'''[[Festival du Film de Paris|Paris Film Festival]]'''\n*1978: \"Best Actress\" \u2013 Geraldine Chaplin\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|0078150|Remember My Name}}\n*{{rotten-tomatoes|remember_my_name}}\n* {{Amg movie|107572|Remember My Name}}\n*{{tcmdb title|id=3909|title=Remember My Name}}\n\n{{Alan Rudolph}}\n\n[[Category:1978 films]]\n[[Category:1970s thriller films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American thriller films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Alan Rudolph]]\n[[Category:American films about revenge]]\n[[Category:Films about stalking]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Remember_My_Name"}
{"title_page": "Abdul-Rahman Al-Sudais", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[Excellency|His Excellency]]<br />[[Sheikh]]\n| name = Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais\n| native_name = [https://geonewsinurdu.co \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0631\u062d\u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u062f\u064a\u0633]\n| native_name_lang = ar\n| image = File:Sudais.png\n| caption = \n<!-- -->\n| order = General President for the Affairs of the Two Holy Mosques\n| monarch = [[Abdullah of Saudi Arabia|King Abdullah]]<br />[[Salman of Saudi Arabia|King Salman]]\n| deputy = {{plainlist |\n* Muhammad Al Khuzaim <small>(retired)</small>\n* Saad Al Mahameed <small>(acting)</small>\n}}\n| term_end = \n| term_start = 8 May 2011&nbsp;\u2013 present\n| predecessor = \n| successor = <!-- -->\n| order1 = Commander-in-Chief of the Special Forces for the security of the Two Holy Mosques\n<!-- -->\n| office2 = Imam of [[Masjid Al Haram]]\n| monarch2 = [[Fahad of Saudi Arabia|King Fahad]]<br />[[Abdullah of Saudi Arabia|King Abdullah]]<br />[[Salman of Saudi Arabia|King Salman]]\n| term_start2 = 1984&nbsp;\u2013 present\n<!-- -->\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1960|2|10|df=y}}<ref name = \"DIHQA\"/>\n| birth_place = [[Riyadh]], [[Saudi Arabia]]\n| resting_place = \n| nationality = [[Saudi Arabian]] {{flagicon|KSA}}\n| website = https://www.gph.gov.sa\n| Denomilal = Salafi\n| Movemet = Salafi\n| School = Salafi\n| width = \n| Follow = Hanbali madhhab}}\n'''Abdul Rahman Ibn Abdul Aziz al-Sudais''' ({{lang-ar|\u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064f \u0671\u0644\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0646 \u0625\u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064f \u0671\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0632\u0650\u064a\u0632\u064f \u0671\u0644\u0633\u064f\u0651\u062f\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0633|\u02bbAbd ar-Rahman ibn \u02bbAbd al-Aziz as-Sudais}}; born 10 February 1960 in [[Riyadh]], [[Saudi Arabia]])<ref name=\"DIHQA\">{{cite web\n|url=http://quran.gov.ae/content/view/94/49/lang,english/\n|title=Ninth Session\n|accessdate=2007-03-19\n|year=2006\n|publisher=[[Dubai International Holy Quran Award]]\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070711191653/http://quran.gov.ae/content/view/94/49/lang%2Cenglish/\n|archivedate=2007-07-11\n|url-status=dead\n}}</ref>\nis the [[imam]] of the [[Masjid al-Haram|Grand Mosque]] in [[Mecca]], [[Saudi Arabia]]; the president of the General Presidency for the Affairs of the Two Holy Mosques;<ref name = \"President\">{{cite web\n| url = https://www.gph.gov.sa/ar-sa/Pages/news-details.aspx?nID=16899\n| title = Maeali Alrayiys Aleami Yareaa Alhafl Alkhitamiu Likhariji Aljameiat Alkhayriat Litahfiz Alquran Alkarim Bialriyad\n| last = <!-- Staff writer -->\n| date = October 3, 2016\n| language = Arabic\n| script-title = ar:\u0645\u0639\u0627\u0644\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0626\u064a\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0645 \u064a\u0631\u0639\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0641\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u062a\u0627\u0645\u064a \u0644\u062e\u0631\u064a\u062c\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0645\u0639\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u064a\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u0644\u062a\u062d\u0641\u064a\u0638 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0631\u0622\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0631\u064a\u0645 \u0628\u0627\u0644\u0631\u064a\u0627\u0636\n| trans-title = His Excellency the President-General sponsors the closing ceremony of the graduates of the Holy Quran Memorization Association in Riyadh\n| access-date = May 29, 2018\n}}\n</ref> a renowned [[q\u0101ri\u02be]] (reciter of the [[Qur'an]]);<ref name=\"bio-assabile\">{{cite web|title=Biography of Abdul Rahman Al Sudais|url=http://www.assabile.com/abdul-rahman-al-sudais-12/abdul-rahman-al-sudais.htm|website=Assabile|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\nand was the Dubai International [[Holy Qur'an]] Award's \"Islamic Personality Of the Year\" in 2005. Al-Sudais has preached Islam's opposition to \"explosions and terrorism\",<ref name=\"ArabNewsASTerrorFight\">{{cite news\n|title=Fight terrorism jointly: Al-Sudais\n|url=http://archive.arabnews.com/?page=1&section=0&article=126344&d=12&m=9&y=2009\n|newspaper=[[Arab News]]\n|location=[[Saudi Arabia]]\n|issn=0254-833X\n|oclc=4574467\n|date=September 12, 2009\n|accessdate=January 22, 2012\n|quote=More than three million Muslim faithful attended juma, taraweeh and Qiyamullail prayers at the Two Holy Mosques on Friday as the imam of the Grand Mosque in Makkah called for joint efforts to combat terrorism.\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110117143436/http://archive.arabnews.com/?page=1&section=0&article=126344&d=12&m=9&y=2009\n|archivedate=January 17, 2011\n}}\n</ref><ref name=\"SGAS\">{{cite news\n|title=Al-Sudais to offer 10 solutions to terrorism\n|first=Taleb\n|last=Bin Mahfouz\n|url=http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentID=2010032467269\n|newspaper=[[Saudi Gazette]]\n|location=[[Saudi Arabia]]\n|issn=1319-0326\n|accessdate=January 22, 2012\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714183218/http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentID=2010032467269\n|archivedate=July 14, 2014\n}}\n</ref> and has called for peaceful inter-faith dialogue,<ref name = \"ArabNewsPrayer\">{{cite news\n| title = Sudais Leads Prayers for Inter-Faith Peace and Harmony\n| url = http://www.arabnews.com/node/250963\n| newspaper = [[Arab News]]\n| location = [[Saudi Arabia]]\n| issn = 0254-833X\n| oclc = 4574467\n| date = June 12, 2004\n| accessdate = October 19, 2014\n| quote = More than three million Muslims attended jumu'ah, taraweeh and Qiyam al-Layl prayers at the Two Sacred Mosques on Friday as the imam of the Grand Mosque in Makkah called for joint efforts to combat terrorism.\u2026Also on hand for the launch of the 10-million-pound ($18 million) London Muslim Center were guests including\u2026Racial Equality Minister Fiona Mactaggart. Prince Charles, in Washington for the funeral of former US President Ronald Reagan, also took part by way of a pre-recorded message.\n}}</ref>\nbut also been sharply criticized for vilifying non-Muslims and especially Jews in his sermons.<ref name=\"panorama\">{{cite interview\n| last = Sacranie\n| first = Iqbal\n| subjectlink = Iqbal Sacranie\n| last2 = Abdul Bari\n| first2 = Muhammad\n| subjectlink2 = Muhammad Abdul Bari\n| last3 = Kantharia\n| first3 = Mehboob\n| last4 = Siddiqui\n| first4 = Ghayasuddin\n| interviewer = John Ware\n| title = A Question of Leadership\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/programmes/panorama/4171950.stm\n| work = [[Panorama (TV series)|Panorama]]\n| publisher = [[BBC]]\n| location = [[London, England]]\n| date = August 21, 2005\n| accessdate=2007-03-30\n| quote = <br />'''Sheikh Abdur-Rahman Al-Sudais, Imam, Ka'ba, Mecca, Saudi Arabia''': The history of Islam is the best testament to how different communities can live together in peace and harmony. Muslims must exemplify the true image of Islam in their interaction with other communities.<br /><br />'''John Ware''': Sheikh Sudais is a leading Imam from the great mosque in Mecca, Islam's holiest city. He had one voice for his Western audience - another for his followers in Saudi.<br /><br />'''Sheikh Abdur-Rahman Al-Sudais''': The worst\u2026of the enemies of Islam are those\u2026whom he\u2026made monkeys and pigs, the aggressive Jews and oppressive Zionists and those that follow them: the callers of the trinity and the cross worshippers\u2026those influenced by the rottenness of their ideas, and the poison of their cultures the followers of secularism\u2026how can we talk sweetly when the Hindus and the idol worshippers kuffar\u2026indulge in their overwhelming hatred against our brothers\u2026in Muslim Kashmir\u2026}}\n</ref><ref name = \"Telegraph Moore\">{{cite news\n| url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/main.jhtml?xml=/opinion/2005/07/09/do09.xml&page=2\n| title = Where is the Gandhi of Islam?\n| accessdate = 2008-10-31\n| last = Moore\n| first = Charles\n| authorlink = Charles Moore (journalist)\n| date = July 9, 2005\n| newspaper = The Daily Telegraph\n| quote = In Mecca two years ago, al Sudais described Jews as \u2018scum of the earth\u2019, \u2018rats of the world\u2019 and \u2018monkeys and pigs who should be annihilated\u2019. Yet, criticise Al Sudais, and Mohammed Abdul Bari leaps furiously to his defence.}}</ref>\nHe has denounced the treatment of Palestinians by Israeli settlers and the state of [[Israel]],<ref name = \"AJCCUN\">{{cite web\n|url = http://www.ccun.org/News/2010/November/13%20n/Shaikh%20Al-Sudais,%20Imam%20of%20Al-Haram%20Mosque%20in%20Makkah%20Calls%20on%20Muslims%20to%20Work%20Towards%20Lifting%20Israeli%20Siege%20of%20Gaza,%20and%20Liberation%20of%20Al-Aqsa%20Mosque.htm\n|title = Shaikh Al-Sudais, Imam of Al-Haram Mosque in Makkah Calls on Muslims to Work Towards Lifting Israeli Siege of Gaza, and Liberation of Al-Aqsa Mosque\n|date=November 2010\n|work = Cross-Cultural Understanding\n|publisher = [[Al-Jazeerah]]\n|accessdate = January 22, 2012\n|quote = The Sheikh demanded an end to the Israeli siege against the Gaza Strip, calling on the Palestinians to unite and put aside their differences.\u2026Calling for the liberation of Palestine, Al-Sudais said now is the time for Palestinian factions to bury their differences. 'These differences have only added to the miseries of our brothers and sisters in Palestine. This inhuman blockade has made life hellish for them.'\n}}</ref>\nand called for more aid to be sent to Palestinians.<ref name=\"ArabNewsGaza\">{{cite news\n|title=Sudais Warns of Gaza Catastrophe\n|last=Ghafour\n|first=Abdul\n|url=http://archive.arabnews.com/?page=1&section=0&article=106374&d=2&m=2&y=2008\n|newspaper=[[Arab News]]\n|location=[[Saudi Arabia]]\n|issn=0254-833X\n|oclc=4574467\n|date=February 2, 2008\n|accessdate=January 22, 2012\n|quote=The imam rebuked Western countries that speak profusely about human rights, freedom and democratic values for keeping mum on the continuing Israeli atrocities in occupied Palestinian territories. Delivering his Juma sermon to the thousands of faithful who thronged the large mosque complex, the imam called for quick delivery of relief supplies such as food and medicine to the people of Gaza. \"Our brothers in Gaza are facing death and destruction, hunger and siege\u2026After God, only you can boost their morale and save them from this trial,\" Al-Sudais told Muslims all over the world. \"Help them, donate for them, especially in this harsh weather condition. They are living in dark without electricity, hunger and poverty. They don't have water or food and medicine. The economic siege has made their lives extremely difficult,\" the Saudi Press Agency quoted the imam as saying.\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120616061137/http://archive.arabnews.com/?page=1\n|archivedate=June 16, 2012\n}}</ref>\nHe has also been noted for identifying women's un-Islamic behavior as in part responsible for the winter 2006 drought in Saudi Arabia.<ref name=\"Bradley\">\n{{cite book\n|last1= Bradley\n|first1= John R.\n|author-link1= John R. Bradley\n|year= 2006\n|chapter= 8. The Segregation of the Sexes\n|title= Saudi Arabia Exposed : Inside a Kingdom in Crisis\n|url = https://www.amazon.com/Saudi-Arabia-Exposed-Kingdom-Updated/dp/1403970777/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1492785712&sr=1-1&keywords=Saudi+Arabia+Exposed+%3A+Inside+a+Kingdom+in+Crisis%2C+Updated+Edition\n|edition= Updated\n|publisher= [[St. Martin's Press|St. Martin's Griffin]]\n|page= 170\n|isbn= 978-1403970770\n|access-date= April 21, 2017\n|via= Amazon preview\n|quote= This was taken up a while later when one of the Imams of the grand mosque in Mecca, Abdul Rahman Al-Sudeis, singled out women as he recited a catalogue of sins responsible for a drought the kingdom was experiencing. Their sins, he said, included 'unveiling, mingling with men, and being indifferent to the hijab.'\n}}\n</ref><ref name = \"Elhadj\">\n{{cite book\n|last1=Elhadj\n|first1=Elie\n|title=The Islamic Shield: Arab Resistance to Democratic and Religious Reforms\n|year = 2007\n|isbn = 1599424118\n|publisher=Universal Publishers\n|page=126\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S2kZfdrEBlAC&pg=PA126&lpg=PA126&dq=al-sudeis+imam+women+drought&source=bl&ots=tZZ5ILpIeC&sig=aP-OB-crc-BaJbJ60IXOgyvB5uY&hl=en&sa=X&ei=HcZBVNe6DYSeyAT694DwCg&ved=0CCMQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=al-sudeis%20imam%20women%20drought&f=false\n|quote= Also deplorable is the explanation given by Dr. A. R. al-Sudais, the Imam and preacher of Islam's holiest mosque in Mecca, regarding the causes behind the severe drought that hit Saudi Arabia in the winter of 2006. On November 13, 2006, a day of prayer to send rain (''{{transl|ar|Istisqua}}'''), Al-Sudais preached that the drought is caused by the proliferation of sin in Saudi society: specifically, dealing in usury, bribery, lying, dishonesty, and violating God's rules.}}</ref> In 2016, he delivered the very important [[Hajj]] sermon to a multitude of pilgrims gathered at [[Mount Arafat|Arafat]] after prayers.<ref name=\"Haj-Sudais\">{{cite news\n| author =<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->\n| title = Haj sermon calls for unity as pilgrims fill Arafat\n| url = http://www.arabnews.com/node/983216/saudi-arabia\n| work = [[Arab News]]\n| location = [[Riyadh]]\n| date = September 11, 2016\n| access-date = June 4, 2018\n}}\n</ref><ref name=\"HajSudaisReuters\">{{cite news\n| last = Nehme\n| first = Dahlia\n| title = Haj pilgrims begin rite which caused deadly crush\n| url = https://www.reuters.com/article/us-saudi-haj-idUSKCN11H0BJ\n| work = [[Reuters]]\n| location = [[London]]\n| date = September 11, 2016\n| access-date = June 4, 2018\n}}\n</ref><!--[[Ahlul Hadidth]]<ref name = \"DIHQA\"/><ref name = \"Ahlul Hadidth\">{{cite news |title=Deviant ideology has no place in Islam: Al-Sudais |url=http://www.arabnews.com/featured/news/649916 |newspaper=[[Arab News]] |date=October 25, 2014 |access-date=June 23, 2015 |quote =Sheikh Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais, head of the Presidency of the Two Holy Mosques, said Hanafism reflected the true Islamic way of life suited to any time or place.\u2026Al-Sudais said the Kingdom has been holding fast to the Hanafi creed and the teachings of Sheikh Muhammad bin Abdul Wahhab who called on people to follow the path of Tawhid and faith.}}</ref> Whahabi<ref>{{cite news|last1=Johnson|first1=Andrew|title=Saudis risk new Muslim divide|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/saudis-risk-new-muslim-division-with-proposal-to-move-mohameds-tomb-9705120.html|accessdate=August 6, 2015|agency=The Independent|date=1 September 2014|quote=King Abdullah has appointed the prominent Wahhabi cleric and imam of the Grand Mosque, Abdul Rahman al-Sudais, to oversee the expansion project\u2026|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150327220241/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/saudis-risk-new-muslim-division-with-proposal-to-move-mohameds-tomb-9705120.html|archive-date=March 27, 2015}}</ref>-->\n\n==Life and career==\nAl-Sudais comes from the [[Anazzah]] clan, and he had [[Hafiz (Quran)|memorized the Quran]] by the age of 12.<ref name = \"DIHQA\" /> Growing up in [[Riyadh]], Al-Sudais studied at the Al Muthana Bin Harith Elementary School, and afterwards the Riyadh Scientific Institution from which he graduated in 1979 with a grade of excellent.<ref name = \"DIHQA\" /> He obtained a degree in [[Sharia]] from [[Riyadh University]] in 1983, his [[Master's degree|Master's]] in Islamic fundamentals from the Sharia College of [[Imam Muhammad bin Saud Islamic University]] in 1987 and received his [[Doctor of Philosophy|Ph.D.]] in Islamic Sharia from [[Umm al-Qura University]] in 1995 while working there as an assistant professor after serving at Riyadh University.<ref name = \"DIHQA\" />\n\nSudais took up his imamate in 1984, at just 22-years of age, and conducted his first sermon at the Grand Mosque in Mecca in July 1984, other than this Sheikh [[Saud Al-Shuraim]] - has been his partner in Taraweeh Prayers from 1991 till 2006, and again in 2014.<ref name=profile/>\n\nIn 2005, Al-Sudais was named by the [[Dubai International Holy Quran Award]] (DIHQA) Organising Committee as its 9th annual \"Islamic Personality Of the Year\" in recognition of his devotion to the Quran and Islam.<ref name = \"DIHQA\" /> When accepting his award in [[Dubai]], he said: \"The message of Islam and Muslims is modesty, fairness, security, stability, sympathy, harmony and kindness.\"<ref name=zaza>{{cite web\n|url=http://archive.gulfnews.com/articles/05/10/24/188472.html\n|title=Islam 'will never support terror or violence'\n|first=Bassam\n|last=Za'za'\n|work=[[Gulf News]]\n|date=October 24, 2005\n|accessdate=January 22, 2012\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071108210204/http://archive.gulfnews.com/articles/05/10/24/188472.html\n|archivedate=November 8, 2007\n}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2010 to 2012, he visited India, Pakistan, Malaysia and Britain. Among his activities has been hosting a seminar at the Higher Institute for Advanced Islamic Studies in Malaysia in 2011, where he spoke about Islamic civilization against the backdrop of modern challenges.<ref name=profile/>\n\nHe was appointed head of the \"Presidency for the Two Holy Mosques at the rank of minister\" by royal decree on 8 May 2012.<ref name=profile>{{cite web|title=Profile: Sheikh Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais|url=http://www.aawsat.net/2012/05/article55242127|website=aawsat.net|publisher=Asharq Al-Awsat|accessdate=19 October 2014|date=9 May 2012}}</ref> He is also a member of the Arabic Language Academy at Mecca.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.m-a-arabia.com/site/8488.html|title= \u0623.\u062f. \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0631\u062d\u0645\u0646 \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u062f\u064a\u0633|publisher= Official website of the Academy|date= 9 February 2015|accessdate= 8 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[Abdul Razzaq al-Mahdi]], Nabil Al-Awadi, [[Tariq Abdelhaleem]], and [[Hani al-Sibai]] who are linked to Al-Qaeda, in addition to others like [[Adnan al-Aroor]], [[Abd Al-Aziz Al-Fawzan]], [[Mohamad al-Arefe]], Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais, [[Abdul-Aziz ibn Abdullah Al Shaykh]] and others were included on a death list by ISIS.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/isis-launches-campaign-calling-kill-prominent-islamic-clerics-such-yousuf-al-qaradawi-saudi |title= ISIS Launches Campaign Calling To Kill Prominent Islamic Clerics Such As Yousuf Al-Qaradawi, Saudi Mufti 'Abd Al-'Aziz Aal Al-Sheikh, Former Egyptian Chief Mufti 'Ali Gum'a |date=February 14, 2017 |number=Special Dispatch No.6781 |website=MEMRI |access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Al-Sudais supervised the film [[One Day In The Haram]], a film about the [[Masjid Al Haram|Haram in Makkah]], told through the eyes of the workers.<ref name = HaramFilm>{{Cite web\n|url=http://twasul.info/872627/\n|script-title=ar:\u062a\u0643\u0634\u0641 \u062a\u0641\u0627\u0635\u064a\u0644 \u0623\u0636\u062e\u0645 \u0639\u0645\u0644 \u0633\u064a\u0646\u0645\u0627\u0626\u064a \u00ab\u064a\u0648\u0645 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062d\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0645\n|title=takshif tafasil 'adkham eamal sinamayiyun ywum fi alharam\n|trans-title=The details of the largest film \"Day in the Haram\" are revealed\n|language=ar\n|date=August 5, 2017\n|access-date=June 4, 2018\n}}\n</ref>\n\n==Views, statements, prayers==\n\n===Conflict resolution among Muslims===\nIn 2003, Sudais stated that he believes that youth need to be taught [[Sharia|Islamic law]], including the precepts of the prohibition on killing oneself and the prohibition against attacking non-Muslims living in Islamic countries. Sudais has also said that Islamic youth should not \"indiscriminately hurl the label of atheism and not to confuse between legitimate jihad and\u2026the terrorizing of peaceable people.\"<ref name = \"Sudais-Aljazeera\">{{cite web\n| url = http://english.aljazeera.net/archive/2003/07/200841010166264771.html\n| title = Mecca police chief to head Saudi security\n| accessdate = 2008-11-04\n| date = July 12, 2003\n| publisher = [[Al Jazeera]]\n}}\n</ref>\n\nSudais has said that there is no room for extremism and sectarianism in Islam and that Islam teaches a moderate path. He said the solution to problems that Muslims face in [[State of Palestine|Palestine]], [[Somalia]], [[Iraq]], [[Kashmir]] and [[Afghanistan]] lies in following the teachings of Islam in letter and spirit. He called for resolution of conflicts through dialogue and negotiations taking into consideration the social and economic benefits that can be achieved by resolving these disputes.<ref name = \"APP\">{{cite web\n|url = http://www.app.com.pk/en/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=9998&Itemid=2\n|title = No room for sectarianism, extremism in Islam : Imam-e-Kaaba\n|date = June 1, 2007\n|publisher = [[Associated Press of Pakistan]]\n|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070927192853/http://www.app.com.pk/en/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=9998&Itemid=2\n|archivedate = September 2007\n|accessdate = January 22, 2012\n|quote = Imam-e-Kaaba, Al-Sheikh Abdur Rehman Al-Sudais Friday said there is no room for sectarianism and extremism in Islam and called upon Muslims to adopt moderate approach to meet challenges. \"Islam rejects sectarianism and extremism, and focuses on adopting a moderate path in accordance with teachings of Islam,\" He said in his 'Juma prayer sermon' at Faisal mosque. ... He called for resolution of conflicts through dialogue and negotiations taking into consideration the social and economic benefits that can be achieved by resolving these disputes.\n}}\n</ref>\n\nSudais also criticized the [[Lal Masjid, Islamabad|Lal Masjid]] administration during the 2007 [[Siege of Lal Masjid#After 2006|Red Mosque crisis]] in Islamabad, Pakistan. He urged the militants and the government to agree to a peaceful resolution through dialogue and urged both parties to protect peace.<ref>Wajid, Ali Wajid.[http://archive.gulfnews.com/articles/07/06/04/10129871.html Imam slams Lal Masjid over standoff] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929124526/http://archive.gulfnews.com/articles/07/06/04/10129871.html |date=September 29, 2007}}. ''Gulf News''.</ref>\n\nSudais is also known for his sermons calling on believers to help other Muslims in war-torn regions.<ref name = \"ArabNewsGaza\" />\nHe has actively spoken out against the persecution of Palestinians by Israeli settlers and the state of Israel,<ref name = \"AJCCUN\"/> and has pleaded for medical supplies and food to be sent to the Palestinians.<ref name = \"ArabNewsGaza\"/>\n\n===Sin and drought===\nIn a sermon on November 13, 2006, Al-Sudais preached that the ongoing drought was caused by the proliferation of sin in Saudi society<ref name = \"Elhadj\" /> and the behavior of women in the kingdom who allegedly were \"unveiling, mingling with men, and being indifferent to the hijab.\"<ref name=\"Bradley\" />\n\n===Prayers for inter-faith peace===\nIn June 2004, Sudais led a following of 10,000 in prayers for inter-faith peace and harmony in London. Racial Equality Minister [[Fiona Mactaggart]] attended Sudais' sermon at the [[East London Mosque]]. [[Prince Charles]], who was in Washington, took part by a pre-recorded message<ref name = \"ArabNewsPrayer\" /> Britain's chief [[Rabbi]], [[Jonathan Sacks]], sent a message of support.<ref name = \"SacksGuardian\">{{cite web\n|url = https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/belief/2009/aug/04/sheikh-sudais-saudi-islam\n|title = Sheikh al-Sudais: coming to a mosque near you\n|first = Riazat\n|last = Butt\n|date = August 4, 2009\n|work = [[The Guardian]]\n|accessdate = January 9, 2012\n|quote = \u2026the Chief Rabbi Sir Jonathan Sacks sent a message of support.\u2026This article was amended on 6 August 2009. The original article wrongly said that Jonathan Sacks attended the al-Sudais sermon at the East London Mosque. This has been corrected.\n}}\n</ref>\n\n===Prayers for the destruction of the Jews===\nIn his sermon of April 19, 2002, broadcast on [[Saudi 1]], Al-Sudais called the Jews \"monkeys and pigs,\" among other invective.<ref name = NM>{{cite web\n|url= https://www.newsmax.com/emerson/saudi-mecca-london/2009/08/07/id/332204/\n|title= Saudi Cleric's London Sermon Draws Fire\n|last= Emerson\n|first= Steve\n|date= August 7, 2009\n|access-date= May 29, 2018\n}}</ref><blockquote>Read the history and you will know that yesterday's Jews were bad predecessors and today's Jews are worse successors. They are killers of prophets and the scum of the earth. God hurled his curses and indignation on them and made them monkeys and pigs and worshippers ''[sic]'' of tyrants. These are the Jews, a continuous lineage of meanness, cunning, obstinacy, tyranny, evil, and corruption.\u2026May God's curses follow them until the Day of Judgement.\u2026Thus, they deserve the curse of God, His angels, and all people.<ref name=\"Sermon1\">{{cite book\n|last1= Anti-Defamation League\n|author-link1= Anti-Defamation League\n|year= 2008\n|chapter= Islamic Antisemtism in Historical Perspective\n|chapter-url= https://books.google.com/books?id=9YFaCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA211&lpg=PA211&dq=Sudais+Sermons+April+19,+2002&source=bl&ots=HTHP2YEtOX&sig=hIC4PVj-6g3fPkZDCTd2c0Xw7xg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi604aPzavbAhUJuVkKHRh6CvcQ6AEIRzAE#v=onepage&q=Sudais%20Sermons%20April%2019%2C%202002&f=false\n|chapter-format=[[Google Books]]\n|editor1-last= Perry\n|editor1-first= Marvin\n|editor1-link= <!-- This is not Marvin Perry the kickboxer -->\n|editor2-last= Negrin\n|editor2-first= Howard E.\n|editor2-link= <!-- This is Howard E. Negrin -->\n|title= The Theory and Practice of Islamic Terrorism: An Anthology\n|publisher= [[Macmillan Publishers|Palgrave Macmillan US]]\n|page= 211\n|lccn = 2008000349\n|isbn= 978-0230608641\n|access-date= May 29, 2018\n|quote=Read the history and you will know that yesterday's Jews were bad predecessors and today's Jews are worse successors. They are killers of prophets and the scum of the earth. God hurled his curses and indignation on them and made them monkeys and pigs and worshippers ''[sic]'' of tyrants. These are the Jews, a continuous lineage of meanness, cunning, obstinacy, tyranny, evil, and corruption. They sow corruption on earth. O Muslims, the Islamic nation today is at the peak of conflict with the enemies of yesterday, today, and tomorrow, with the grandsons of Bani-Quraydah, Al-Nadiri, and Qaynuqa [Jewish tribes in the early days of Islam]. May God's curses follow them until the Day of Judgement. The conflict is exploding and magnifying, the exploitation and greed are increasing, and the indulgence in humbling Arabs and Muslims and their holy places has become very serious by the world rodents that have revoked pacts and agreements. Treachery, sabotage, and cunning dominate their minds and injustice and tyranny flow in their veins. They cannot but remain arrogant, reckless, corrupt, and harmful. Thus, they deserve the curse of God, His angels, and all people.\n}}</ref></blockquote> He has prayed to God to \"terminate\" the Jews and has claimed that the Israelis aspired to tear down the [[al-Aqsa mosque]] and build their temple upon its ruins.<ref name = \"IBB\"/>\n\n===Call for all-out war against Shiites===\nOn March 31, 2015, an audio recording of al-Sudais was circulated online. The caption on the photo accompanying the recording read \"Imam of the grand mosque in Mecca calls for all-out war against [[Shiites]].\" In the recording, al-Sudais called for an all-out war against Shias:<ref name= \"YahooF\">{{cite web|url= https://finance.yahoo.com/news/muslim-cleric-calls-war-101500065.html|title= Muslim Cleric Calls for \u2018All-Out War\u2019\n|work= [[Yahoo! Finance]]|publisher= [[Yahoo!]]|date= April 2, 2015|accessdate= May 27, 2015}}</ref><ref name= \"Fiscal\">{{cite news|url= http://www.thefiscaltimes.com/2015/04/02/Muslim-Cleric-Calls-All-Out-War|title= Muslim Cleric Calls for \u2018All-Out War\u2019|author= Riyadh Mohammed|work= [[The Fiscal Times]]|date= April 2, 2015|accessdate= May 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|Our war with Iran, say that out loud, is a war between Sunnis and Shiites. Our war with Iran...is truly sectarian. If it was not sectarian, we will make it sectarian... The Jews and cross (referring to Christians)... I swear by Allah that they will have their days... The prophet said Rome will be conquered... Our disagreement with [[Rafidha]] (another word for Shiites) will not be removed nor our suicide to fight them...as long as they are on the face of the earth...}}\n\n==Controversy==\n\n===Anti-semitism===\nFollowing his 2002 speech, Al-Sudais has been described as an antisemite<ref name=\"CFAC\">{{cite web\n|url=http://www.antisemitism.org.il/eng/events/9162/Canada_%E2%80%93_A_Saudi_Imam_is_Banned_From_Entering_the_Country\n|title=Canada \u2013 A Saudi Imam is Banned From Entering the Country\n|accessdate=2007-03-18\n|date=May 18, 2004\n|publisher=Coordination Forum for Countering Antisemitism\n|quote=1=The Canadian Government has decided to prevent the entry into the country Sheikh Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais, the Imam of the Great Mosque of Mecca, because of his preaching of hatred of the Jews.\u2026The decision to ban the Imam's entry into Canada is part of the authorities' campaign against antisemitism, in the light of recent events in Toronto and Montreal, and against racist incitement in general.\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928001618/http://www.antisemitism.org.il/eng/events/9162/Canada_%E2%80%93_A_Saudi_Imam_is_Banned_From_Entering_the_Country\n|archivedate=2007-09-28\n}}\n</ref><ref name = \"AN\">{{cite web\n|url=http://www.arabnews.com/node/249729\n| title = Canadian Embassy Denies Refusing Sheikh Al-Sudais Visa\n| accessdate = August 22, 2012\n| date = May 20, 2004\n| quote =1=The issue of Sheikh Al-Sudais\u2019 visit was raised during the question hour at the Canadian Parliament recently. A Canadian legislator, Jason Kenney, called on the government to block the entry of the Islamic scholar to Canada on the grounds that some of his sermons were anti-Semitic.\n}}\n</ref> for publicly praying to God to \u2018terminate\u2019 the Jews, whom he called \"the scum of humanity\u2026the rats of the world\u2026prophet killers\u2026pigs and monkeys\",<ref name = \"IBB\" /><ref name = \"OrlSent\">{{cite web\n|url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/2003-12-03/news/0312030409_1_keynote-speaker-islamic-shah\n| title = Islamic Conference Speaker Draws Wrath\n| last = Jacobson\n| first = Susan\n| accessdate = August 22, 2012\n| date = December 3, 2003\n| quote =1=Some anti-hate groups are outraged that a Saudi cleric who called on God to \"terminate\" the Jews and urged Muslims to shun peace with Israel is the invited keynote speaker at an Islamic conference scheduled this month in Osceola County.\n}}\n</ref><ref name = \"Russert\" /> and as a result has been barred from conferences in the United States and been refused entry to Canada.<ref name = \"CFAC\" />\n\nAl-Sudais has been listed as an example of [[Islam and Antisemitism|theological anti-Semitism]] by the [[Anti-Defamation League]], when he called curses down upon Jews and labeled them \"scum of the earth\" in his sermons.<ref name=\"Sermon1\" />\n\nThe [[International Broadcasting Bureau]] also has reported the antisemitism of Sudais's April 2002 sermon.<ref name = \"IBB\">{{cite web\n|url=http://www.ibb.gov/editorials/09844.htm\n| title = Saudi Imam Preaches Hate\n| accessdate = 2007-03-28\n| date = April 25, 2002\n| publisher = [[International Broadcasting Bureau]]\n| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070712171807/http://www.ibb.gov/editorials/09844.htm\n| archivedate = July 12, 2007\n| quote = On April 19th, a prominent Saudi imam said in a sermon broadcast on radio and television that Arabs \u2018must say farewell to peace initiatives\u2019 with the Jewish state. Even worse, the sermon by Sheikh Abdulrahman Al-Sudais [shake ahb-d\u2019l-RAHKH-mahn ah-soo-DAYSS] was filled with anti-Semitic vitriol. Preaching at the Grand Mosque in Mecca, Islam's holiest shrine, Sheikh Sudais called Jews \u2018the scum of humanity\u2026the rats of the world\u2026prophet killers\u2026pigs and monkeys.\u2019 He prayed to God to \"terminate\" the Jews. In addition to spewing such villainous bile, Sheikh Sudais also claimed falsely that the Israelis \u2018aspire to tear down the al-Aqsa mosque [in Jerusalem] to build their so-called temple on its ruins.\u2019 In fact, the Israeli government has never expressed any interest in tearing down the mosque, which is built near the ruins of a Jewish temple. On the contrary, Israel respects Muslim holy sites and has pledged to keep them accessible to all.\n}}</ref>\n\nIn a May 2003 interview with [[NBC]]'s [[Tim Russert]], the foreign policy adviser to the Saudi crown prince, [[Adel al-Jubeir]], confirmed al-Sudais's statements, agreed that they were \"clearly not right,\" and stated that he was reprimanded, but was still allowed to preach. He also said that \"if he [Sudais] had a choice he would retract these words - he would not have said these words.\"<ref name = \"Russert\">\n {{cite interview\n| last = Al-Jubeir\n| first = Adel\n| subjectlink = Adel al-Jubeir\n| interviewer = [[Tim Russert]]\n| title = Adel Al-Jubeir, Foreign Policy Advisor to Crown Prince Abdullah on NBC's \u2018Meet the Press\u2019\n|url=http://www.saudiembassy.net/2003News/Statements/TransDetail.asp?cIndex=190\n| work = [[Meet the Press]]\n| publisher = [[NBC]]\n| location = [[Washington, DC]]\n| date = May 18, 2003\n| accessdate=March 30, 2007\n| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071212183932/http://www.saudiembassy.net/2003News/Statements/TransDetail.asp?cIndex=190\n| archivedate = December 12, 2007}}\n<br />\n'''MR. RUSSERT:''' But it went on and on, and you mention imams in Saudi Arabia. This is what a top Saudi Arabian religious leader said, using inflammatory anti-Semitic rhetoric -- \"Pray to Allah to terminate Jews. Urge all Muslims to shun peace with Israel.\" Shaikh Abdelrahman al-Sudais, one of the top imams in Saudi Arabia, called on Muslims to say farewell to peace initiatives with these people, Jews. He prayed to the Muslim God to terminate the Jews, whom he called the scum of humanity, rats of the world, prophet killers, pigs and monkeys.\n<br />\n'''MR. AL-JUBEIR:''' That's also incorrect. And he was reprimanded for this.\n<br />\n'''MR. RUSSERT:''' He was reprimanded?\n<br />\n'''MR. AL-JUBEIR:''' Oh, yes.\n<br />\n'''MR. RUSSERT:''' Is he still preaching?\n<br />\n'''MR. AL-JUBEIR:''' Yes, he is. But he's not \u2013 I think if he had a choice he would retract these words \u2013 he would not have said these words. It's clearly not right. You cannot \u2013 you cannot defile, you cannot malign other people, certainly not when it comes to their faith.\n</ref>\n\nAl-Sudais has not only attacked Jews, but other non-Muslims, such as [[Hindu]]s and [[Christians]]. John Ware on the [[BBC]] program ''[[Panorama (TV series)|Panorama]]'' entitled \"A Question of Leadership\" from August 21, 2005, cited Al-Sudais referring disparagingly to Christians as \"cross-worshippers\" and Hindus as \"idol worshippers.\"<ref name=\"panorama\" /> Ware pointed out the discrepancy between Sudais's sermons to Saudis with his speech to Western audiences.<ref name=\"panorama\" />\n\nThe [[Muslim Council of Britain]] questioned the veracity of quotes given in the interview, calling them \"deliberately garbled\" and the program as a whole \"deeply unfair.\"<ref name=\"MCB\">{{cite press release\n|publisher=[[Muslim Council of Britain]]\n|date=August 20, 2005\n|title=John Ware's Panorama programme - A witch-hunt against British Muslims\n|url=http://www.mcb.org.uk/media/presstext.php?ann_id=160\n|accessdate=January 22, 2012\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120317073821/http://www.mcb.org.uk/media/presstext.php?ann_id=160\n|archivedate=March 17, 2012\n}}</ref>\nThe council urged caution, and while condemning any form of anti-semitic remarks, requested verification that these words were indeed spoken by Al-Sudais.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.mcb.org.uk/uploads/Panorama_response.doc\n|title=A Look At John Ware's Panorama Programme About British Muslims\n|accessdate=2007-03-28\n|date=August 21, 2006\n|format=[[Microsoft Word]]\n|publisher=[[Muslim Council of Britain]]\n|page=5\n|quote='''Anti-semitic Remarks'''<br />The Muslim Council of Britain strongly abhors any form of racism, including anti-semitism. Islam as a faith is famously colour-blind and was revealed to bring peoples of all nations together in worship of the One True God. Ware quotes the Imam of the Ka\u2019bah as making allegedly anti-semitic remarks. If this was the case then we would condemn them completely. However, based on Ware's \u2018selective\u2019 quotations which we have highlighted earlier in this response we would urge caution and verification that these were indeed uttered by the Imam of the Ka\u2019bah.\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927041544/http://www.mcb.org.uk/uploads/Panorama_response.doc\n|archivedate=September 27, 2007\n}}</ref>\nAfter a series of exchanges, the [[BBC]]'s ''[[Panorama (TV series)|Panorama]]'' editor, Mike Robinson, posted a response to each of the Muslim Council's allegations, accusing them of \"unwarranted and wildly inaccurate attacks\" and \"bad faith allegations.\"<ref name=BBCresponse>{{cite web\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/panorama/4297490.stm\n| title = Response to MCB complaints\n| accessdate = 2007-03-28\n| last = Robinson\n| first = Mike\n| date = September 30, 2005\n| publisher = BBC\n| quote = You have claimed that the programme maligned certain organisations affiliated to the MCB, even though the programme highlighted their sermons, documents and conduct which were sectarian or which demonised other faiths and races, and which were likely to foment division. Such views were either advocated by these affiliates or appeared to be tolerated by them. You have also publicly accused us of being engaged in a \"Witch-hunt against British Muslims.\" I simply cannot accept that highlighting sectarian and racist language amounts to persecution. You have expressed scepticism that Sheikh Al Sudais, who was an honoured guest at the East London Mosque where the MCB's Deputy General Secretary is Chairman, had previously said in Mecca that Jews were \"monkeys and pigs\", \"rats of the world\" and the \"offspring of apes and pigs\"; that Christians were \"cross worshippers\u2026those influenced by the rottenness of their ideas and the poison of their cultures the followers of secularism\", and that Hindus were \"idol worshippers.\" I can assure you that he did. His sermons are available from a Saudi website covering mosques in the holy cities of Medina and Mecca and the translation we used was verified by BBC Monitoring, a fluent Arab speaker on our production team, and a translator outside the BBC.}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2009, the [[Board of Deputies of British Jews]] protested a visit by Al-Sudais to Britain in which he gave lectures at several mosques and attended an event with Tory MP [[Tony Baldry]]. Baldry subsequently defended his decision to work with Al-Sudais, stating that \"If I had written a text of what a moderate Muslim would say, his would have been a word-perfect example.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/hate-shiekh%E2%80%99s-british-tour-sparks-outrage |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304204405/http://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/hate-shiekh%E2%80%99s-british-tour-sparks-outrage |archive-date=2016-03-04 |title=Hate Shiekh's British tour sparks outrage |first=Leon |last=Symons |newspaper=[[Jewish Chronicle]] |date= August 6, 2009}}</ref>\n\n=== Comments against Shiites ===\n\nOn 31 March 2015, an audio recording of al-Sudais was circulated online. The caption on photo accompanying the recording read \"Imam of the grand mosque in Mecca calls for all-out war against [[Shiites]].\" In the recording al-Sudais called for an all-out war against Shias.\nIn view of these statements against Shiites by al-Sudais,\nAhmed Abdul Hussein, the editor-in-chief of an Iraqi news agency warned about the Shiite-Sunni conflict, \"Remember the date 3/31/2015, the day the Shiite-Sunni war was announced. It will last more than [[Crusades|crusade wars]].\"<ref name= \"YahooF\"/><ref name= \"Fiscal\"/>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Saudi Arabia|Biography|Islam}}\n* [[Masjid al-Haram]]\n* [[Qur'an reading]]\n* [[Saud Al-Shuraim]]\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n*[https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Abdul_Rahman_Ibn_Abdul_Aziz_Al_Sudais_The_Holy_Qur?id=Bbhxczmb4xkecvg3k3kxnrjubji Quran recitation by Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais on Google Play (free listening and free download)]\n*[http://www.haramain.info/search/label/%D8%B4%D9%8A%D8%AE%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%B3%20-%20Sheikh%20Sudais?max-results=5 Salaat and other recordings (Audio / Video) Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais]\n*[http://mp3quran.net/eng/sds_english.html Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais Recitation of complete Quran]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070314025519/http://memri.org/bin/articles.cgi?Page=archives&Area=sr&ID=SR01102 Based on Koranic Verses, Interpretations, and Traditions, Muslim Clerics State: The Jews Are the Descendants of Apes, Pigs, And Other Animals] by Aluma Solnick ([[MEMRI]] Special Report - No. 11. November 1, 2002\n*[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/programmes/panorama/4171950.stm A question of leadership] (BBC. Panorama) August 21, 2005\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071008132552/http://www.islamicthinkers.com/index/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=441&Itemid=74 Statement of the Islamic Thinkers Society on As-Sudais]\n\n{{Hanbali scholars}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sudais, Abdul Rahman Al-}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Islam and antisemitism]]\n[[Category:Saudi Arabian imams]]\n[[Category:Saudi Arabian Muslims]]\n[[Category:20th-century imams]]\n[[Category:21st-century imams]]\n[[Category:People who memorized the Quran]]\n[[Category:Saudi Arabian Quran reciters]]\n[[Category:People from Riyadh]]\n[[Category:King Saud University alumni]]\n[[Category:Umm al-Qura University alumni]]\n[[Category:Critics of Shia Islam]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[Excellency|His Excellency]]<br />[[Sheikh]]\n| name = Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais\n| native_name = \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0631\u062d\u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u062f\u064a\u0633\n| native_name_lang = ar\n| image = File:Sudais.png\n| caption = \n<!-- -->\n| order = General President for the Affairs of the Two Holy Mosques\n| monarch = [[Abdullah of Saudi Arabia|King Abdullah]]<br />[[Salman of Saudi Arabia|King Salman]]\n| deputy = {{plainlist |\n* Muhammad Al Khuzaim <small>(retired)</small>\n* Saad Al Mahameed <small>(acting)</small>\n}}\n| term_end = \n| term_start = 8 May 2011&nbsp;\u2013 present\n| predecessor = \n| successor = <!-- -->\n| order1 = Commander-in-Chief of the Special Forces for the security of the Two Holy Mosques\n<!-- -->\n| office2 = Imam of [[Masjid Al Haram]]\n| monarch2 = [[Fahad of Saudi Arabia|King Fahad]]<br />[[Abdullah of Saudi Arabia|King Abdullah]]<br />[[Salman of Saudi Arabia|King Salman]]\n| term_start2 = 1984&nbsp;\u2013 present\n<!-- -->\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1960|2|10|df=y}}<ref name = \"DIHQA\"/>\n| birth_place = [[Riyadh]], [[Saudi Arabia]]\n| resting_place = \n| nationality = [[Saudi Arabian]] {{flagicon|KSA}}\n| website = https://www.gph.gov.sa\n| Denomilal = Salafi\n| Movemet = Salafi\n| School = Salafi\n| width = \n| Follow = Hanbali madhhab}}\n'''Abdul Rahman Ibn Abdul Aziz al-Sudais''' ({{lang-ar|\u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064f \u0671\u0644\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0646 \u0625\u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064f \u0671\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0632\u0650\u064a\u0632\u064f \u0671\u0644\u0633\u064f\u0651\u062f\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0633|\u02bbAbd ar-Rahman ibn \u02bbAbd al-Aziz as-Sudais}}; born 10 February 1960 in [[Riyadh]], [[Saudi Arabia]])<ref name=\"DIHQA\">{{cite web\n|url=http://quran.gov.ae/content/view/94/49/lang,english/\n|title=Ninth Session\n|accessdate=2007-03-19\n|year=2006\n|publisher=[[Dubai International Holy Quran Award]]\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070711191653/http://quran.gov.ae/content/view/94/49/lang%2Cenglish/\n|archivedate=2007-07-11\n|url-status=dead\n}}</ref>\nis the [[imam]] of the [[Masjid al-Haram|Grand Mosque]] in [[Mecca]], [[Saudi Arabia]]; the president of the General Presidency for the Affairs of the Two Holy Mosques;<ref name = \"President\">{{cite web\n| url = https://www.gph.gov.sa/ar-sa/Pages/news-details.aspx?nID=16899\n| title = Maeali Alrayiys Aleami Yareaa Alhafl Alkhitamiu Likhariji Aljameiat Alkhayriat Litahfiz Alquran Alkarim Bialriyad\n| last = <!-- Staff writer -->\n| date = October 3, 2016\n| language = Arabic\n| script-title = ar:\u0645\u0639\u0627\u0644\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0626\u064a\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0645 \u064a\u0631\u0639\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0641\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u062a\u0627\u0645\u064a \u0644\u062e\u0631\u064a\u062c\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0645\u0639\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u064a\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u0644\u062a\u062d\u0641\u064a\u0638 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0631\u0622\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0631\u064a\u0645 \u0628\u0627\u0644\u0631\u064a\u0627\u0636\n| trans-title = His Excellency the President-General sponsors the closing ceremony of the graduates of the Holy Quran Memorization Association in Riyadh\n| access-date = May 29, 2018\n}}\n</ref> a renowned [[q\u0101ri\u02be]] (reciter of the [[Qur'an]]);<ref name=\"bio-assabile\">{{cite web|title=Biography of Abdul Rahman Al Sudais|url=http://www.assabile.com/abdul-rahman-al-sudais-12/abdul-rahman-al-sudais.htm|website=Assabile|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\nand was the Dubai International [[Holy Qur'an]] Award's \"Islamic Personality Of the Year\" in 2005. Al-Sudais has preached Islam's opposition to \"explosions and terrorism\",<ref name=\"ArabNewsASTerrorFight\">{{cite news\n|title=Fight terrorism jointly: Al-Sudais\n|url=http://archive.arabnews.com/?page=1&section=0&article=126344&d=12&m=9&y=2009\n|newspaper=[[Arab News]]\n|location=[[Saudi Arabia]]\n|issn=0254-833X\n|oclc=4574467\n|date=September 12, 2009\n|accessdate=January 22, 2012\n|quote=More than three million Muslim faithful attended juma, taraweeh and Qiyamullail prayers at the Two Holy Mosques on Friday as the imam of the Grand Mosque in Makkah called for joint efforts to combat terrorism.\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110117143436/http://archive.arabnews.com/?page=1&section=0&article=126344&d=12&m=9&y=2009\n|archivedate=January 17, 2011\n}}\n</ref><ref name=\"SGAS\">{{cite news\n|title=Al-Sudais to offer 10 solutions to terrorism\n|first=Taleb\n|last=Bin Mahfouz\n|url=http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentID=2010032467269\n|newspaper=[[Saudi Gazette]]\n|location=[[Saudi Arabia]]\n|issn=1319-0326\n|accessdate=January 22, 2012\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714183218/http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentID=2010032467269\n|archivedate=July 14, 2014\n}}\n</ref> and has called for peaceful inter-faith dialogue,<ref name = \"ArabNewsPrayer\">{{cite news\n| title = Sudais Leads Prayers for Inter-Faith Peace and Harmony\n| url = http://www.arabnews.com/node/250963\n| newspaper = [[Arab News]]\n| location = [[Saudi Arabia]]\n| issn = 0254-833X\n| oclc = 4574467\n| date = June 12, 2004\n| accessdate = October 19, 2014\n| quote = More than three million Muslims attended jumu'ah, taraweeh and Qiyam al-Layl prayers at the Two Sacred Mosques on Friday as the imam of the Grand Mosque in Makkah called for joint efforts to combat terrorism.\u2026Also on hand for the launch of the 10-million-pound ($18 million) London Muslim Center were guests including\u2026Racial Equality Minister Fiona Mactaggart. Prince Charles, in Washington for the funeral of former US President Ronald Reagan, also took part by way of a pre-recorded message.\n}}</ref>\nbut also been sharply criticized for vilifying non-Muslims and especially Jews in his sermons.<ref name=\"panorama\">{{cite interview\n| last = Sacranie\n| first = Iqbal\n| subjectlink = Iqbal Sacranie\n| last2 = Abdul Bari\n| first2 = Muhammad\n| subjectlink2 = Muhammad Abdul Bari\n| last3 = Kantharia\n| first3 = Mehboob\n| last4 = Siddiqui\n| first4 = Ghayasuddin\n| interviewer = John Ware\n| title = A Question of Leadership\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/programmes/panorama/4171950.stm\n| work = [[Panorama (TV series)|Panorama]]\n| publisher = [[BBC]]\n| location = [[London, England]]\n| date = August 21, 2005\n| accessdate=2007-03-30\n| quote = <br />'''Sheikh Abdur-Rahman Al-Sudais, Imam, Ka'ba, Mecca, Saudi Arabia''': The history of Islam is the best testament to how different communities can live together in peace and harmony. Muslims must exemplify the true image of Islam in their interaction with other communities.<br /><br />'''John Ware''': Sheikh Sudais is a leading Imam from the great mosque in Mecca, Islam's holiest city. He had one voice for his Western audience - another for his followers in Saudi.<br /><br />'''Sheikh Abdur-Rahman Al-Sudais''': The worst\u2026of the enemies of Islam are those\u2026whom he\u2026made monkeys and pigs, the aggressive Jews and oppressive Zionists and those that follow them: the callers of the trinity and the cross worshippers\u2026those influenced by the rottenness of their ideas, and the poison of their cultures the followers of secularism\u2026how can we talk sweetly when the Hindus and the idol worshippers kuffar\u2026indulge in their overwhelming hatred against our brothers\u2026in Muslim Kashmir\u2026}}\n</ref><ref name = \"Telegraph Moore\">{{cite news\n| url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/main.jhtml?xml=/opinion/2005/07/09/do09.xml&page=2\n| title = Where is the Gandhi of Islam?\n| accessdate = 2008-10-31\n| last = Moore\n| first = Charles\n| authorlink = Charles Moore (journalist)\n| date = July 9, 2005\n| newspaper = The Daily Telegraph\n| quote = In Mecca two years ago, al Sudais described Jews as \u2018scum of the earth\u2019, \u2018rats of the world\u2019 and \u2018monkeys and pigs who should be annihilated\u2019. Yet, criticise Al Sudais, and Mohammed Abdul Bari leaps furiously to his defence.}}</ref>\nHe has denounced the treatment of Palestinians by Israeli settlers and the state of [[Israel]],<ref name = \"AJCCUN\">{{cite web\n|url = http://www.ccun.org/News/2010/November/13%20n/Shaikh%20Al-Sudais,%20Imam%20of%20Al-Haram%20Mosque%20in%20Makkah%20Calls%20on%20Muslims%20to%20Work%20Towards%20Lifting%20Israeli%20Siege%20of%20Gaza,%20and%20Liberation%20of%20Al-Aqsa%20Mosque.htm\n|title = Shaikh Al-Sudais, Imam of Al-Haram Mosque in Makkah Calls on Muslims to Work Towards Lifting Israeli Siege of Gaza, and Liberation of Al-Aqsa Mosque\n|date=November 2010\n|work = Cross-Cultural Understanding\n|publisher = [[Al-Jazeerah]]\n|accessdate = January 22, 2012\n|quote = The Sheikh demanded an end to the Israeli siege against the Gaza Strip, calling on the Palestinians to unite and put aside their differences.\u2026Calling for the liberation of Palestine, Al-Sudais said now is the time for Palestinian factions to bury their differences. 'These differences have only added to the miseries of our brothers and sisters in Palestine. This inhuman blockade has made life hellish for them.'\n}}</ref>\nand called for more aid to be sent to Palestinians.<ref name=\"ArabNewsGaza\">{{cite news\n|title=Sudais Warns of Gaza Catastrophe\n|last=Ghafour\n|first=Abdul\n|url=http://archive.arabnews.com/?page=1&section=0&article=106374&d=2&m=2&y=2008\n|newspaper=[[Arab News]]\n|location=[[Saudi Arabia]]\n|issn=0254-833X\n|oclc=4574467\n|date=February 2, 2008\n|accessdate=January 22, 2012\n|quote=The imam rebuked Western countries that speak profusely about human rights, freedom and democratic values for keeping mum on the continuing Israeli atrocities in occupied Palestinian territories. Delivering his Juma sermon to the thousands of faithful who thronged the large mosque complex, the imam called for quick delivery of relief supplies such as food and medicine to the people of Gaza. \"Our brothers in Gaza are facing death and destruction, hunger and siege\u2026After God, only you can boost their morale and save them from this trial,\" Al-Sudais told Muslims all over the world. \"Help them, donate for them, especially in this harsh weather condition. They are living in dark without electricity, hunger and poverty. They don't have water or food and medicine. The economic siege has made their lives extremely difficult,\" the Saudi Press Agency quoted the imam as saying.\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120616061137/http://archive.arabnews.com/?page=1\n|archivedate=June 16, 2012\n}}</ref>\nHe has also been noted for identifying women's un-Islamic behavior as in part responsible for the winter 2006 drought in Saudi Arabia.<ref name=\"Bradley\">\n{{cite book\n|last1= Bradley\n|first1= John R.\n|author-link1= John R. Bradley\n|year= 2006\n|chapter= 8. The Segregation of the Sexes\n|title= Saudi Arabia Exposed : Inside a Kingdom in Crisis\n|url = https://www.amazon.com/Saudi-Arabia-Exposed-Kingdom-Updated/dp/1403970777/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1492785712&sr=1-1&keywords=Saudi+Arabia+Exposed+%3A+Inside+a+Kingdom+in+Crisis%2C+Updated+Edition\n|edition= Updated\n|publisher= [[St. Martin's Press|St. Martin's Griffin]]\n|page= 170\n|isbn= 978-1403970770\n|access-date= April 21, 2017\n|via= Amazon preview\n|quote= This was taken up a while later when one of the Imams of the grand mosque in Mecca, Abdul Rahman Al-Sudeis, singled out women as he recited a catalogue of sins responsible for a drought the kingdom was experiencing. Their sins, he said, included 'unveiling, mingling with men, and being indifferent to the hijab.'\n}}\n</ref><ref name = \"Elhadj\">\n{{cite book\n|last1=Elhadj\n|first1=Elie\n|title=The Islamic Shield: Arab Resistance to Democratic and Religious Reforms\n|year = 2007\n|isbn = 1599424118\n|publisher=Universal Publishers\n|page=126\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S2kZfdrEBlAC&pg=PA126&lpg=PA126&dq=al-sudeis+imam+women+drought&source=bl&ots=tZZ5ILpIeC&sig=aP-OB-crc-BaJbJ60IXOgyvB5uY&hl=en&sa=X&ei=HcZBVNe6DYSeyAT694DwCg&ved=0CCMQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=al-sudeis%20imam%20women%20drought&f=false\n|quote= Also deplorable is the explanation given by Dr. A. R. al-Sudais, the Imam and preacher of Islam's holiest mosque in Mecca, regarding the causes behind the severe drought that hit Saudi Arabia in the winter of 2006. On November 13, 2006, a day of prayer to send rain (''{{transl|ar|Istisqua}}'''), Al-Sudais preached that the drought is caused by the proliferation of sin in Saudi society: specifically, dealing in usury, bribery, lying, dishonesty, and violating God's rules.}}</ref> In 2016, he delivered the very important [[Hajj]] sermon to a multitude of pilgrims gathered at [[Mount Arafat|Arafat]] after prayers.<ref name=\"Haj-Sudais\">{{cite news\n| author =<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->\n| title = Haj sermon calls for unity as pilgrims fill Arafat\n| url = http://www.arabnews.com/node/983216/saudi-arabia\n| work = [[Arab News]]\n| location = [[Riyadh]]\n| date = September 11, 2016\n| access-date = June 4, 2018\n}}\n</ref><ref name=\"HajSudaisReuters\">{{cite news\n| last = Nehme\n| first = Dahlia\n| title = Haj pilgrims begin rite which caused deadly crush\n| url = https://www.reuters.com/article/us-saudi-haj-idUSKCN11H0BJ\n| work = [[Reuters]]\n| location = [[London]]\n| date = September 11, 2016\n| access-date = June 4, 2018\n}}\n</ref><!--[[Ahlul Hadidth]]<ref name = \"DIHQA\"/><ref name = \"Ahlul Hadidth\">{{cite news |title=Deviant ideology has no place in Islam: Al-Sudais |url=http://www.arabnews.com/featured/news/649916 |newspaper=[[Arab News]] |date=October 25, 2014 |access-date=June 23, 2015 |quote =Sheikh Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais, head of the Presidency of the Two Holy Mosques, said Hanafism reflected the true Islamic way of life suited to any time or place.\u2026Al-Sudais said the Kingdom has been holding fast to the Hanafi creed and the teachings of Sheikh Muhammad bin Abdul Wahhab who called on people to follow the path of Tawhid and faith.}}</ref> Whahabi<ref>{{cite news|last1=Johnson|first1=Andrew|title=Saudis risk new Muslim divide|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/saudis-risk-new-muslim-division-with-proposal-to-move-mohameds-tomb-9705120.html|accessdate=August 6, 2015|agency=The Independent|date=1 September 2014|quote=King Abdullah has appointed the prominent Wahhabi cleric and imam of the Grand Mosque, Abdul Rahman al-Sudais, to oversee the expansion project\u2026|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150327220241/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/saudis-risk-new-muslim-division-with-proposal-to-move-mohameds-tomb-9705120.html|archive-date=March 27, 2015}}</ref>-->\n\n==Life and career==\nAl-Sudais comes from the [[Anazzah]] clan, and he had [[Hafiz (Quran)|memorized the Quran]] by the age of 12.<ref name = \"DIHQA\" /> Growing up in [[Riyadh]], Al-Sudais studied at the Al Muthana Bin Harith Elementary School, and afterwards the Riyadh Scientific Institution from which he graduated in 1979 with a grade of excellent.<ref name = \"DIHQA\" /> He obtained a degree in [[Sharia]] from [[Riyadh University]] in 1983, his [[Master's degree|Master's]] in Islamic fundamentals from the Sharia College of [[Imam Muhammad bin Saud Islamic University]] in 1987 and received his [[Doctor of Philosophy|Ph.D.]] in Islamic Sharia from [[Umm al-Qura University]] in 1995 while working there as an assistant professor after serving at Riyadh University.<ref name = \"DIHQA\" />\n\nSudais took up his imamate in 1984, at just 22-years of age, and conducted his first sermon at the Grand Mosque in Mecca in July 1984, other than this Sheikh [[Saud Al-Shuraim]] - has been his partner in Taraweeh Prayers from 1991 till 2006, and again in 2014.<ref name=profile/>\n\nIn 2005, Al-Sudais was named by the [[Dubai International Holy Quran Award]] (DIHQA) Organising Committee as its 9th annual \"Islamic Personality Of the Year\" in recognition of his devotion to the Quran and Islam.<ref name = \"DIHQA\" /> When accepting his award in [[Dubai]], he said: \"The message of Islam and Muslims is modesty, fairness, security, stability, sympathy, harmony and kindness.\"<ref name=zaza>{{cite web\n|url=http://archive.gulfnews.com/articles/05/10/24/188472.html\n|title=Islam 'will never support terror or violence'\n|first=Bassam\n|last=Za'za'\n|work=[[Gulf News]]\n|date=October 24, 2005\n|accessdate=January 22, 2012\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071108210204/http://archive.gulfnews.com/articles/05/10/24/188472.html\n|archivedate=November 8, 2007\n}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2010 to 2012, he visited India, Pakistan, Malaysia and Britain. Among his activities has been hosting a seminar at the Higher Institute for Advanced Islamic Studies in Malaysia in 2011, where he spoke about Islamic civilization against the backdrop of modern challenges.<ref name=profile/>\n\nHe was appointed head of the \"Presidency for the Two Holy Mosques at the rank of minister\" by royal decree on 8 May 2012.<ref name=profile>{{cite web|title=Profile: Sheikh Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais|url=http://www.aawsat.net/2012/05/article55242127|website=aawsat.net|publisher=Asharq Al-Awsat|accessdate=19 October 2014|date=9 May 2012}}</ref> He is also a member of the Arabic Language Academy at Mecca.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.m-a-arabia.com/site/8488.html|title= \u0623.\u062f. \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0631\u062d\u0645\u0646 \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u062f\u064a\u0633|publisher= Official website of the Academy|date= 9 February 2015|accessdate= 8 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[Abdul Razzaq al-Mahdi]], Nabil Al-Awadi, [[Tariq Abdelhaleem]], and [[Hani al-Sibai]] who are linked to Al-Qaeda, in addition to others like [[Adnan al-Aroor]], [[Abd Al-Aziz Al-Fawzan]], [[Mohamad al-Arefe]], Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais, [[Abdul-Aziz ibn Abdullah Al Shaykh]] and others were included on a death list by ISIS.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/isis-launches-campaign-calling-kill-prominent-islamic-clerics-such-yousuf-al-qaradawi-saudi |title= ISIS Launches Campaign Calling To Kill Prominent Islamic Clerics Such As Yousuf Al-Qaradawi, Saudi Mufti 'Abd Al-'Aziz Aal Al-Sheikh, Former Egyptian Chief Mufti 'Ali Gum'a |date=February 14, 2017 |number=Special Dispatch No.6781 |website=MEMRI |access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Al-Sudais supervised the film [[One Day In The Haram]], a film about the [[Masjid Al Haram|Haram in Makkah]], told through the eyes of the workers.<ref name = HaramFilm>{{Cite web\n|url=http://twasul.info/872627/\n|script-title=ar:\u062a\u0643\u0634\u0641 \u062a\u0641\u0627\u0635\u064a\u0644 \u0623\u0636\u062e\u0645 \u0639\u0645\u0644 \u0633\u064a\u0646\u0645\u0627\u0626\u064a \u00ab\u064a\u0648\u0645 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062d\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0645\n|title=takshif tafasil 'adkham eamal sinamayiyun ywum fi alharam\n|trans-title=The details of the largest film \"Day in the Haram\" are revealed\n|language=ar\n|date=August 5, 2017\n|access-date=June 4, 2018\n}}\n</ref>\n\n==Views, statements, prayers==\n\n===Conflict resolution among Muslims===\nIn 2003, Sudais stated that he believes that youth need to be taught [[Sharia|Islamic law]], including the precepts of the prohibition on killing oneself and the prohibition against attacking non-Muslims living in Islamic countries. Sudais has also said that Islamic youth should not \"indiscriminately hurl the label of atheism and not to confuse between legitimate jihad and\u2026the terrorizing of peaceable people.\"<ref name = \"Sudais-Aljazeera\">{{cite web\n| url = http://english.aljazeera.net/archive/2003/07/200841010166264771.html\n| title = Mecca police chief to head Saudi security\n| accessdate = 2008-11-04\n| date = July 12, 2003\n| publisher = [[Al Jazeera]]\n}}\n</ref>\n\nSudais has said that there is no room for extremism and sectarianism in Islam and that Islam teaches a moderate path. He said the solution to problems that Muslims face in [[State of Palestine|Palestine]], [[Somalia]], [[Iraq]], [[Kashmir]] and [[Afghanistan]] lies in following the teachings of Islam in letter and spirit. He called for resolution of conflicts through dialogue and negotiations taking into consideration the social and economic benefits that can be achieved by resolving these disputes.<ref name = \"APP\">{{cite web\n|url = http://www.app.com.pk/en/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=9998&Itemid=2\n|title = No room for sectarianism, extremism in Islam : Imam-e-Kaaba\n|date = June 1, 2007\n|publisher = [[Associated Press of Pakistan]]\n|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070927192853/http://www.app.com.pk/en/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=9998&Itemid=2\n|archivedate = September 2007\n|accessdate = January 22, 2012\n|quote = Imam-e-Kaaba, Al-Sheikh Abdur Rehman Al-Sudais Friday said there is no room for sectarianism and extremism in Islam and called upon Muslims to adopt moderate approach to meet challenges. \"Islam rejects sectarianism and extremism, and focuses on adopting a moderate path in accordance with teachings of Islam,\" He said in his 'Juma prayer sermon' at Faisal mosque. ... He called for resolution of conflicts through dialogue and negotiations taking into consideration the social and economic benefits that can be achieved by resolving these disputes.\n}}\n</ref>\n\nSudais also criticized the [[Lal Masjid, Islamabad|Lal Masjid]] administration during the 2007 [[Siege of Lal Masjid#After 2006|Red Mosque crisis]] in Islamabad, Pakistan. He urged the militants and the government to agree to a peaceful resolution through dialogue and urged both parties to protect peace.<ref>Wajid, Ali Wajid.[http://archive.gulfnews.com/articles/07/06/04/10129871.html Imam slams Lal Masjid over standoff] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929124526/http://archive.gulfnews.com/articles/07/06/04/10129871.html |date=September 29, 2007}}. ''Gulf News''.</ref>\n\nSudais is also known for his sermons calling on believers to help other Muslims in war-torn regions.<ref name = \"ArabNewsGaza\" />\nHe has actively spoken out against the persecution of Palestinians by Israeli settlers and the state of Israel,<ref name = \"AJCCUN\"/> and has pleaded for medical supplies and food to be sent to the Palestinians.<ref name = \"ArabNewsGaza\"/>\n\n===Sin and drought===\nIn a sermon on November 13, 2006, Al-Sudais preached that the ongoing drought was caused by the proliferation of sin in Saudi society<ref name = \"Elhadj\" /> and the behavior of women in the kingdom who allegedly were \"unveiling, mingling with men, and being indifferent to the hijab.\"<ref name=\"Bradley\" />\n\n===Prayers for inter-faith peace===\nIn June 2004, Sudais led a following of 10,000 in prayers for inter-faith peace and harmony in London. Racial Equality Minister [[Fiona Mactaggart]] attended Sudais' sermon at the [[East London Mosque]]. [[Prince Charles]], who was in Washington, took part by a pre-recorded message<ref name = \"ArabNewsPrayer\" /> Britain's chief [[Rabbi]], [[Jonathan Sacks]], sent a message of support.<ref name = \"SacksGuardian\">{{cite web\n|url = https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/belief/2009/aug/04/sheikh-sudais-saudi-islam\n|title = Sheikh al-Sudais: coming to a mosque near you\n|first = Riazat\n|last = Butt\n|date = August 4, 2009\n|work = [[The Guardian]]\n|accessdate = January 9, 2012\n|quote = \u2026the Chief Rabbi Sir Jonathan Sacks sent a message of support.\u2026This article was amended on 6 August 2009. The original article wrongly said that Jonathan Sacks attended the al-Sudais sermon at the East London Mosque. This has been corrected.\n}}\n</ref>\n\n===Prayers for the destruction of the Jews===\nIn his sermon of April 19, 2002, broadcast on [[Saudi 1]], Al-Sudais called the Jews \"monkeys and pigs,\" among other invective.<ref name = NM>{{cite web\n|url= https://www.newsmax.com/emerson/saudi-mecca-london/2009/08/07/id/332204/\n|title= Saudi Cleric's London Sermon Draws Fire\n|last= Emerson\n|first= Steve\n|date= August 7, 2009\n|access-date= May 29, 2018\n}}</ref><blockquote>Read the history and you will know that yesterday's Jews were bad predecessors and today's Jews are worse successors. They are killers of prophets and the scum of the earth. God hurled his curses and indignation on them and made them monkeys and pigs and worshippers ''[sic]'' of tyrants. These are the Jews, a continuous lineage of meanness, cunning, obstinacy, tyranny, evil, and corruption.\u2026May God's curses follow them until the Day of Judgement.\u2026Thus, they deserve the curse of God, His angels, and all people.<ref name=\"Sermon1\">{{cite book\n|last1= Anti-Defamation League\n|author-link1= Anti-Defamation League\n|year= 2008\n|chapter= Islamic Antisemtism in Historical Perspective\n|chapter-url= https://books.google.com/books?id=9YFaCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA211&lpg=PA211&dq=Sudais+Sermons+April+19,+2002&source=bl&ots=HTHP2YEtOX&sig=hIC4PVj-6g3fPkZDCTd2c0Xw7xg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi604aPzavbAhUJuVkKHRh6CvcQ6AEIRzAE#v=onepage&q=Sudais%20Sermons%20April%2019%2C%202002&f=false\n|chapter-format=[[Google Books]]\n|editor1-last= Perry\n|editor1-first= Marvin\n|editor1-link= <!-- This is not Marvin Perry the kickboxer -->\n|editor2-last= Negrin\n|editor2-first= Howard E.\n|editor2-link= <!-- This is Howard E. Negrin -->\n|title= The Theory and Practice of Islamic Terrorism: An Anthology\n|publisher= [[Macmillan Publishers|Palgrave Macmillan US]]\n|page= 211\n|lccn = 2008000349\n|isbn= 978-0230608641\n|access-date= May 29, 2018\n|quote=Read the history and you will know that yesterday's Jews were bad predecessors and today's Jews are worse successors. They are killers of prophets and the scum of the earth. God hurled his curses and indignation on them and made them monkeys and pigs and worshippers ''[sic]'' of tyrants. These are the Jews, a continuous lineage of meanness, cunning, obstinacy, tyranny, evil, and corruption. They sow corruption on earth. O Muslims, the Islamic nation today is at the peak of conflict with the enemies of yesterday, today, and tomorrow, with the grandsons of Bani-Quraydah, Al-Nadiri, and Qaynuqa [Jewish tribes in the early days of Islam]. May God's curses follow them until the Day of Judgement. The conflict is exploding and magnifying, the exploitation and greed are increasing, and the indulgence in humbling Arabs and Muslims and their holy places has become very serious by the world rodents that have revoked pacts and agreements. Treachery, sabotage, and cunning dominate their minds and injustice and tyranny flow in their veins. They cannot but remain arrogant, reckless, corrupt, and harmful. Thus, they deserve the curse of God, His angels, and all people.\n}}</ref></blockquote> He has prayed to God to \"terminate\" the Jews and has claimed that the Israelis aspired to tear down the [[al-Aqsa mosque]] and build their temple upon its ruins.<ref name = \"IBB\"/>\n\n===Call for all-out war against Shiites===\nOn March 31, 2015, an audio recording of al-Sudais was circulated online. The caption on the photo accompanying the recording read \"Imam of the grand mosque in Mecca calls for all-out war against [[Shiites]].\" In the recording, al-Sudais called for an all-out war against Shias:<ref name= \"YahooF\">{{cite web|url= https://finance.yahoo.com/news/muslim-cleric-calls-war-101500065.html|title= Muslim Cleric Calls for \u2018All-Out War\u2019\n|work= [[Yahoo! Finance]]|publisher= [[Yahoo!]]|date= April 2, 2015|accessdate= May 27, 2015}}</ref><ref name= \"Fiscal\">{{cite news|url= http://www.thefiscaltimes.com/2015/04/02/Muslim-Cleric-Calls-All-Out-War|title= Muslim Cleric Calls for \u2018All-Out War\u2019|author= Riyadh Mohammed|work= [[The Fiscal Times]]|date= April 2, 2015|accessdate= May 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|Our war with Iran, say that out loud, is a war between Sunnis and Shiites. Our war with Iran...is truly sectarian. If it was not sectarian, we will make it sectarian... The Jews and cross (referring to Christians)... I swear by Allah that they will have their days... The prophet said Rome will be conquered... Our disagreement with [[Rafidha]] (another word for Shiites) will not be removed nor our suicide to fight them...as long as they are on the face of the earth...}}\n\n==Controversy==\n\n===Anti-semitism===\nFollowing his 2002 speech, Al-Sudais has been described as an antisemite<ref name=\"CFAC\">{{cite web\n|url=http://www.antisemitism.org.il/eng/events/9162/Canada_%E2%80%93_A_Saudi_Imam_is_Banned_From_Entering_the_Country\n|title=Canada \u2013 A Saudi Imam is Banned From Entering the Country\n|accessdate=2007-03-18\n|date=May 18, 2004\n|publisher=Coordination Forum for Countering Antisemitism\n|quote=1=The Canadian Government has decided to prevent the entry into the country Sheikh Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais, the Imam of the Great Mosque of Mecca, because of his preaching of hatred of the Jews.\u2026The decision to ban the Imam's entry into Canada is part of the authorities' campaign against antisemitism, in the light of recent events in Toronto and Montreal, and against racist incitement in general.\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928001618/http://www.antisemitism.org.il/eng/events/9162/Canada_%E2%80%93_A_Saudi_Imam_is_Banned_From_Entering_the_Country\n|archivedate=2007-09-28\n}}\n</ref><ref name = \"AN\">{{cite web\n|url=http://www.arabnews.com/node/249729\n| title = Canadian Embassy Denies Refusing Sheikh Al-Sudais Visa\n| accessdate = August 22, 2012\n| date = May 20, 2004\n| quote =1=The issue of Sheikh Al-Sudais\u2019 visit was raised during the question hour at the Canadian Parliament recently. A Canadian legislator, Jason Kenney, called on the government to block the entry of the Islamic scholar to Canada on the grounds that some of his sermons were anti-Semitic.\n}}\n</ref> for publicly praying to God to \u2018terminate\u2019 the Jews, whom he called \"the scum of humanity\u2026the rats of the world\u2026prophet killers\u2026pigs and monkeys\",<ref name = \"IBB\" /><ref name = \"OrlSent\">{{cite web\n|url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/2003-12-03/news/0312030409_1_keynote-speaker-islamic-shah\n| title = Islamic Conference Speaker Draws Wrath\n| last = Jacobson\n| first = Susan\n| accessdate = August 22, 2012\n| date = December 3, 2003\n| quote =1=Some anti-hate groups are outraged that a Saudi cleric who called on God to \"terminate\" the Jews and urged Muslims to shun peace with Israel is the invited keynote speaker at an Islamic conference scheduled this month in Osceola County.\n}}\n</ref><ref name = \"Russert\" /> and as a result has been barred from conferences in the United States and been refused entry to Canada.<ref name = \"CFAC\" />\n\nAl-Sudais has been listed as an example of [[Islam and Antisemitism|theological anti-Semitism]] by the [[Anti-Defamation League]], when he called curses down upon Jews and labeled them \"scum of the earth\" in his sermons.<ref name=\"Sermon1\" />\n\nThe [[International Broadcasting Bureau]] also has reported the antisemitism of Sudais's April 2002 sermon.<ref name = \"IBB\">{{cite web\n|url=http://www.ibb.gov/editorials/09844.htm\n| title = Saudi Imam Preaches Hate\n| accessdate = 2007-03-28\n| date = April 25, 2002\n| publisher = [[International Broadcasting Bureau]]\n| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070712171807/http://www.ibb.gov/editorials/09844.htm\n| archivedate = July 12, 2007\n| quote = On April 19th, a prominent Saudi imam said in a sermon broadcast on radio and television that Arabs \u2018must say farewell to peace initiatives\u2019 with the Jewish state. Even worse, the sermon by Sheikh Abdulrahman Al-Sudais [shake ahb-d\u2019l-RAHKH-mahn ah-soo-DAYSS] was filled with anti-Semitic vitriol. Preaching at the Grand Mosque in Mecca, Islam's holiest shrine, Sheikh Sudais called Jews \u2018the scum of humanity\u2026the rats of the world\u2026prophet killers\u2026pigs and monkeys.\u2019 He prayed to God to \"terminate\" the Jews. In addition to spewing such villainous bile, Sheikh Sudais also claimed falsely that the Israelis \u2018aspire to tear down the al-Aqsa mosque [in Jerusalem] to build their so-called temple on its ruins.\u2019 In fact, the Israeli government has never expressed any interest in tearing down the mosque, which is built near the ruins of a Jewish temple. On the contrary, Israel respects Muslim holy sites and has pledged to keep them accessible to all.\n}}</ref>\n\nIn a May 2003 interview with [[NBC]]'s [[Tim Russert]], the foreign policy adviser to the Saudi crown prince, [[Adel al-Jubeir]], confirmed al-Sudais's statements, agreed that they were \"clearly not right,\" and stated that he was reprimanded, but was still allowed to preach. He also said that \"if he [Sudais] had a choice he would retract these words - he would not have said these words.\"<ref name = \"Russert\">\n {{cite interview\n| last = Al-Jubeir\n| first = Adel\n| subjectlink = Adel al-Jubeir\n| interviewer = [[Tim Russert]]\n| title = Adel Al-Jubeir, Foreign Policy Advisor to Crown Prince Abdullah on NBC's \u2018Meet the Press\u2019\n|url=http://www.saudiembassy.net/2003News/Statements/TransDetail.asp?cIndex=190\n| work = [[Meet the Press]]\n| publisher = [[NBC]]\n| location = [[Washington, DC]]\n| date = May 18, 2003\n| accessdate=March 30, 2007\n| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071212183932/http://www.saudiembassy.net/2003News/Statements/TransDetail.asp?cIndex=190\n| archivedate = December 12, 2007}}\n<br />\n'''MR. RUSSERT:''' But it went on and on, and you mention imams in Saudi Arabia. This is what a top Saudi Arabian religious leader said, using inflammatory anti-Semitic rhetoric -- \"Pray to Allah to terminate Jews. Urge all Muslims to shun peace with Israel.\" Shaikh Abdelrahman al-Sudais, one of the top imams in Saudi Arabia, called on Muslims to say farewell to peace initiatives with these people, Jews. He prayed to the Muslim God to terminate the Jews, whom he called the scum of humanity, rats of the world, prophet killers, pigs and monkeys.\n<br />\n'''MR. AL-JUBEIR:''' That's also incorrect. And he was reprimanded for this.\n<br />\n'''MR. RUSSERT:''' He was reprimanded?\n<br />\n'''MR. AL-JUBEIR:''' Oh, yes.\n<br />\n'''MR. RUSSERT:''' Is he still preaching?\n<br />\n'''MR. AL-JUBEIR:''' Yes, he is. But he's not \u2013 I think if he had a choice he would retract these words \u2013 he would not have said these words. It's clearly not right. You cannot \u2013 you cannot defile, you cannot malign other people, certainly not when it comes to their faith.\n</ref>\n\nAl-Sudais has not only attacked Jews, but other non-Muslims, such as [[Hindu]]s and [[Christians]]. John Ware on the [[BBC]] program ''[[Panorama (TV series)|Panorama]]'' entitled \"A Question of Leadership\" from August 21, 2005, cited Al-Sudais referring disparagingly to Christians as \"cross-worshippers\" and Hindus as \"idol worshippers.\"<ref name=\"panorama\" /> Ware pointed out the discrepancy between Sudais's sermons to Saudis with his speech to Western audiences.<ref name=\"panorama\" />\n\nThe [[Muslim Council of Britain]] questioned the veracity of quotes given in the interview, calling them \"deliberately garbled\" and the program as a whole \"deeply unfair.\"<ref name=\"MCB\">{{cite press release\n|publisher=[[Muslim Council of Britain]]\n|date=August 20, 2005\n|title=John Ware's Panorama programme - A witch-hunt against British Muslims\n|url=http://www.mcb.org.uk/media/presstext.php?ann_id=160\n|accessdate=January 22, 2012\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120317073821/http://www.mcb.org.uk/media/presstext.php?ann_id=160\n|archivedate=March 17, 2012\n}}</ref>\nThe council urged caution, and while condemning any form of anti-semitic remarks, requested verification that these words were indeed spoken by Al-Sudais.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.mcb.org.uk/uploads/Panorama_response.doc\n|title=A Look At John Ware's Panorama Programme About British Muslims\n|accessdate=2007-03-28\n|date=August 21, 2006\n|format=[[Microsoft Word]]\n|publisher=[[Muslim Council of Britain]]\n|page=5\n|quote='''Anti-semitic Remarks'''<br />The Muslim Council of Britain strongly abhors any form of racism, including anti-semitism. Islam as a faith is famously colour-blind and was revealed to bring peoples of all nations together in worship of the One True God. Ware quotes the Imam of the Ka\u2019bah as making allegedly anti-semitic remarks. If this was the case then we would condemn them completely. However, based on Ware's \u2018selective\u2019 quotations which we have highlighted earlier in this response we would urge caution and verification that these were indeed uttered by the Imam of the Ka\u2019bah.\n|url-status=dead\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927041544/http://www.mcb.org.uk/uploads/Panorama_response.doc\n|archivedate=September 27, 2007\n}}</ref>\nAfter a series of exchanges, the [[BBC]]'s ''[[Panorama (TV series)|Panorama]]'' editor, Mike Robinson, posted a response to each of the Muslim Council's allegations, accusing them of \"unwarranted and wildly inaccurate attacks\" and \"bad faith allegations.\"<ref name=BBCresponse>{{cite web\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/panorama/4297490.stm\n| title = Response to MCB complaints\n| accessdate = 2007-03-28\n| last = Robinson\n| first = Mike\n| date = September 30, 2005\n| publisher = BBC\n| quote = You have claimed that the programme maligned certain organisations affiliated to the MCB, even though the programme highlighted their sermons, documents and conduct which were sectarian or which demonised other faiths and races, and which were likely to foment division. Such views were either advocated by these affiliates or appeared to be tolerated by them. You have also publicly accused us of being engaged in a \"Witch-hunt against British Muslims.\" I simply cannot accept that highlighting sectarian and racist language amounts to persecution. You have expressed scepticism that Sheikh Al Sudais, who was an honoured guest at the East London Mosque where the MCB's Deputy General Secretary is Chairman, had previously said in Mecca that Jews were \"monkeys and pigs\", \"rats of the world\" and the \"offspring of apes and pigs\"; that Christians were \"cross worshippers\u2026those influenced by the rottenness of their ideas and the poison of their cultures the followers of secularism\", and that Hindus were \"idol worshippers.\" I can assure you that he did. His sermons are available from a Saudi website covering mosques in the holy cities of Medina and Mecca and the translation we used was verified by BBC Monitoring, a fluent Arab speaker on our production team, and a translator outside the BBC.}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2009, the [[Board of Deputies of British Jews]] protested a visit by Al-Sudais to Britain in which he gave lectures at several mosques and attended an event with Tory MP [[Tony Baldry]]. Baldry subsequently defended his decision to work with Al-Sudais, stating that \"If I had written a text of what a moderate Muslim would say, his would have been a word-perfect example.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/hate-shiekh%E2%80%99s-british-tour-sparks-outrage |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304204405/http://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/hate-shiekh%E2%80%99s-british-tour-sparks-outrage |archive-date=2016-03-04 |title=Hate Shiekh's British tour sparks outrage |first=Leon |last=Symons |newspaper=[[Jewish Chronicle]] |date= August 6, 2009}}</ref>\n\n=== Comments against Shiites ===\n\nOn 31 March 2015, an audio recording of al-Sudais was circulated online. The caption on photo accompanying the recording read \"Imam of the grand mosque in Mecca calls for all-out war against [[Shiites]].\" In the recording al-Sudais called for an all-out war against Shias.\nIn view of these statements against Shiites by al-Sudais,\nAhmed Abdul Hussein, the editor-in-chief of an Iraqi news agency warned about the Shiite-Sunni conflict, \"Remember the date 3/31/2015, the day the Shiite-Sunni war was announced. It will last more than [[Crusades|crusade wars]].\"<ref name= \"YahooF\"/><ref name= \"Fiscal\"/>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Saudi Arabia|Biography|Islam}}\n* [[Masjid al-Haram]]\n* [[Qur'an reading]]\n* [[Saud Al-Shuraim]]\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n*[https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Abdul_Rahman_Ibn_Abdul_Aziz_Al_Sudais_The_Holy_Qur?id=Bbhxczmb4xkecvg3k3kxnrjubji Quran recitation by Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais on Google Play (free listening and free download)]\n*[http://www.haramain.info/search/label/%D8%B4%D9%8A%D8%AE%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%B3%20-%20Sheikh%20Sudais?max-results=5 Salaat and other recordings (Audio / Video) Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais]\n*[http://mp3quran.net/eng/sds_english.html Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais Recitation of complete Quran]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070314025519/http://memri.org/bin/articles.cgi?Page=archives&Area=sr&ID=SR01102 Based on Koranic Verses, Interpretations, and Traditions, Muslim Clerics State: The Jews Are the Descendants of Apes, Pigs, And Other Animals] by Aluma Solnick ([[MEMRI]] Special Report - No. 11. November 1, 2002\n*[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/programmes/panorama/4171950.stm A question of leadership] (BBC. Panorama) August 21, 2005\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071008132552/http://www.islamicthinkers.com/index/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=441&Itemid=74 Statement of the Islamic Thinkers Society on As-Sudais]\n\n{{Hanbali scholars}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sudais, Abdul Rahman Al-}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Islam and antisemitism]]\n[[Category:Saudi Arabian imams]]\n[[Category:Saudi Arabian Muslims]]\n[[Category:20th-century imams]]\n[[Category:21st-century imams]]\n[[Category:People who memorized the Quran]]\n[[Category:Saudi Arabian Quran reciters]]\n[[Category:People from Riyadh]]\n[[Category:King Saud University alumni]]\n[[Category:Umm al-Qura University alumni]]\n[[Category:Critics of Shia Islam]]\n", "name_user": "86.97.77.189", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Name chany)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdul-Rahman_Al-Sudais"}
{"title_page": "Beecroft Building", "text_new": "[[File:Beecroft Bldg Oxford.jpg|thumb|The Beecroft Building viewed from [[Parks Road]], [[Oxford]]]]\n\nThe '''Beecroft Building'''' is one of the buildings forming part of the [[Department of Physics, University of Oxford|Department of Physics]], [[University of Oxford]] in [[Oxford]], [[England]].<ref name=\"dop\">{{cite web| url=https://www2.physics.ox.ac.uk/the-beecroft-building | title=The Beecroft Building | publisher=[[Department of Physics, University of Oxford]] | location=UK | accessdate=11 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\nThe Beecroft Building is immediately in front of the [[Lindemann Building]] and close to the [[Clarendon Laboratory]] [[Townsend Building, Oxford|Townsend Building]]. It is located on [[Parks Road]] in the [[Science Area, Oxford|Science Area]] of Oxford University. It is next to the [[University Parks]], immediately to the north.\n\nThe Beecroft Building was designed by [[Hawkins\\Brown]] and completed in 2018.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.hawkinsbrown.com/projects/the-beecroft-building | title=Beecroft Building, University of Oxford | publisher=[[Hawkins\\Brown]] | date=2020 | accessdate=10 April 2020 }}</ref> Planet Partitional was also involved with the contract.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.planetpartitioning.co.uk/planet-partitioning-secure-contract-for-beecroft-building/ | title=Planet Partitioning secure contract for University of Oxford\u2019s the Beecroft building | publisher=Planet Partitioning | location=UK | date=14 March 2017 | accessdate=10 April 2020 }}</ref> The budget was approximately \u00a340 million.<ref name=\"dop\" /><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.eocengineers.com/project/beecroft-building-208 | title=The Beecroft Building | website=www.eocengineers.com | publisher=Eckersley O'Callaghan | location=UK | accessdate=28 August 2015 }}</ref>\n\nThe building was opened by Sir [[Tim Berners-Lee]] on 17 September 2018,<ref name=\"dop\" /> in the prescence of Professor [[Louise Richardson]] ([[Vice-Chancellor of Oxford]]), [[Lord Patten of Barnes]] ([[Chancellor of Oxford]]), Professor [[John Wheater]] (Head of the Department of Physics) and [[Adrian Beecroft]] (part-funder of the building).<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OsuMz-Ep7gQ | title=The opening of Oxford's Beecroft Building | author=University of Oxford | author-link=University of Oxford | publisher=[[YouTube]] | date=27 September 2018 | accessdate=11 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\nThe building is named after its part-funder [[Adrian Beecroft]]. The building is specifically focused on [[Theoretical physics|theoretical]], [[Condensed matter physics|condensed matter]] and [[Quantum (physics)|quantum]] physics. According to ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'', the funding for this building was inspired by Beecroft's interest in [[astrophysics]].<ref name=\"telegraph\">{{cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/3664641/The-New-Philanthropists.html | title=The New Philanthropists | last=Thomas | first=David | newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | date=20 April 2007 | access-date=11 April 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.campaign.ox.ac.uk/news/beecroft-building | title=Celebrating the \u2018bottoming out\u2019 of Oxford\u2019s Beecroft Building | website=www.campaign.ox.ac.uk| publisher=Development Office, [[University of Oxford]] | location=UK | date=5 July 2016 | access-date=11 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{coord|51.7598151|N|1.2577957|W|type:landmark_region:GB|display=title}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:2018 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures completed in 2018]]\n[[Category:Departments of the University of Oxford]]\n[[Category:University and college laboratories in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Physics laboratories]]\n\n{{UK-struct-stub}}\n", "text_old": "[[File:Beecroft Bldg Oxford.jpg|thumb|The Beecroft Building viewed from [[Parks Road]], [[Oxford]]]]\n\nThe '''Beecroft Building'''' is one of the buildings forming part of the [[Department of Physics, University of Oxford|Department of Physics]], [[University of Oxford]] in [[Oxford]], [[England]].<ref name=\"dop\">{{cite web| url=https://www2.physics.ox.ac.uk/the-beecroft-building | title=The Beecroft Building | publisher=[[Department of Physics, University of Oxford]] | location=UK | accessdate=11 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\nThe Beecroft Building is immediately in front of the [[Lindemann Building]] and close to the [[Clarendon_Laboratory]]. It is located on [[Parks Road]] in the [[Science Area, Oxford|Science Area]] of Oxford University. It is next to the [[University Parks]], immediately to the north.\n\nThe Beecroft Building was designed by [[Hawkins\\Brown]] and completed in 2018.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.hawkinsbrown.com/projects/the-beecroft-building | title=Beecroft Building, University of Oxford | publisher=[[Hawkins\\Brown]] | date=2020 | accessdate=10 April 2020 }}</ref> Planet Partitional was also involved with the contract.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.planetpartitioning.co.uk/planet-partitioning-secure-contract-for-beecroft-building/ | title=Planet Partitioning secure contract for University of Oxford\u2019s the Beecroft building | publisher=Planet Partitioning | location=UK | date=14 March 2017 | accessdate=10 April 2020 }}</ref> The budget was approximately \u00a340 million.<ref name=\"dop\" /><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.eocengineers.com/project/beecroft-building-208 | title=The Beecroft Building | website=www.eocengineers.com | publisher=Eckersley O'Callaghan | location=UK | accessdate=28 August 2015 }}</ref>\n\nThe building was opened by Sir [[Tim Berners-Lee]] on 17 September 2018,<ref name=\"dop\" /> in the prescence of Professor [[Louise Richardson]] ([[Vice-Chancellor of Oxford]]), [[Lord Patten of Barnes]] ([[Chancellor of Oxford]]), Professor [[John Wheater]] (Head of the Department of Physics) and [[Adrian Beecroft]] (part-funder of the building).<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OsuMz-Ep7gQ | title=The opening of Oxford's Beecroft Building | author=University of Oxford | author-link=University of Oxford | publisher=[[YouTube]] | date=27 September 2018 | accessdate=11 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\nThe building is named after its part-funder [[Adrian Beecroft]]. The building is specifically focused on [[Theoretical physics|theoretical]], [[Condensed matter physics|condensed matter]] and [[Quantum (physics)|quantum]] physics. According to ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'', the funding for this building was inspired by Beecroft's interest in [[astrophysics]].<ref name=\"telegraph\">{{cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/3664641/The-New-Philanthropists.html | title=The New Philanthropists | last=Thomas | first=David | newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | date=20 April 2007 | access-date=11 April 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.campaign.ox.ac.uk/news/beecroft-building | title=Celebrating the \u2018bottoming out\u2019 of Oxford\u2019s Beecroft Building | website=www.campaign.ox.ac.uk| publisher=Development Office, [[University of Oxford]] | location=UK | date=5 July 2016 | access-date=11 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{coord|51.7598151|N|1.2577957|W|type:landmark_region:GB|display=title}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:2018 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures completed in 2018]]\n[[Category:Departments of the University of Oxford]]\n[[Category:University and college laboratories in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Physics laboratories]]\n\n{{UK-struct-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Jpbowen", "label": "safe", "comment": "Location info", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beecroft_Building"}
